('6', '47', 'Erin', 'gnomeloaf@gmail.com', 'http://www.rarelylikable.com', '71.88.51.190', '2009-06-10 21:41:09', '2009-06-11 01:41:09', 'I\'m not sure I\'d have the same answers for \"change your life\" and \"litmag objects of semi-illicit writer-fantasy.\" One has already changed my life because it made me think a lot about what I was (and am sometimes still) afraid to send out. I\'m not sure the New Yorker would do the same. \r\n\r\nWhat\'s *really* interesting to me in that discussion are the \"why I write\" answers. There\'s much wider range than I thought there would be.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042316 Firefox/3.0.10', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('7', '47', 'admin', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://', '71.13.217.52', '2009-06-10 22:08:10', '2009-06-11 02:08:10', 'The range of answers is indeed interesting. It has been one of the better Giant threads I\'ve seen in some time.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042315 Firefox/3.0.10', '', '0', '1', 'N'),
('8', '47', 'admin', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://', '71.13.217.52', '2009-06-10 22:10:37', '2009-06-11 02:10:37', 'I also wanted to add that I can really relate to certain publications challenging what you think about yourself as a writer, and what you\'re willing to send out into the world.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.10) Gecko/2009042315 Firefox/3.0.10', '', '6', '1', 'N'),
