('24', '81', 'Margosita', 'margaret.lafleur@gmail.com', '', '76.21.35.243', '2009-06-21 19:12:19', '2009-06-21 23:12:19', '\"As Americans, we have absolutely no way of truly understanding what it means for a government to be unwilling or unable to transition power peaceully. It is an insult to the people who are losing their lives and living with tyranny to think that a green userpic is a means of showing solidarity.\"\r\n\r\nI agree with that first part, but I don\'t understand the second part.  Insulting?  Empty, maybe.  But considering that many people in Iran don\'t have access to other forms of communication that might be used to otherwise express solidarity, I find it hard to imagine that they are insulted by any kind of show of support.  The people of Iran want to be heard and I think the online movement of replacing userpics is a way to say, \"Hey, someone is hearing you.\"\r\n\r\nI understand that it is frustrating and can play as \"elitist and condescending\", but I also see it as genuine and a way for those of us feel frustrated and angry to say so, through a medium that is heavily in use in Iran, on the streets, right now.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.4; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060214 Firefox/3.0.11', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('25', '81', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-06-21 22:09:09', '2009-06-22 02:09:09', 'I was in a bad mood when I wrote this. I think insulting might be a bit strong. Empty is definitely more what I was going for. I do agree though that it is quite remarkable how the Iranians are using social networking. There will be books written about how things like Twitter facilitated revolution.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060214 Firefox/3.0.11', '', '24', '1', 'N'),
('27', '81', 'krysjez', 'shoryu_happy@yahoo.com.sg', 'http://krysjez.wordpress.com', '220.255.7.143', '2009-06-23 09:55:23', '2009-06-23 13:55:23', 'I think the main problem lies in how half the people who tinted their userpics green did it only because all their friends on Twitter were doing it.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060215 Firefox/3.0.11 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('28', '87', 'Ethel Rohan', 'ethelrohan@gmail.com', '', '24.4.57.196', '2009-06-23 13:01:01', '2009-06-23 17:01:01', 'I listened to the recording, and, sorry!, I\'m still laughing. All right for me from this safe distance, right? That is just sad. \r\n\r\nSeriously, you have my commiserations.  I can\'t imagine what it\'s like to have neighbors like that. I don\'t get people that have no boundaries, that insist on taking up so much obnoxious space in the world. I think how for so much of my life I apologized for the small amount of space I took up, always side-stepping and shrinking myself so as to allow people more than their fair share, literally and figuratively, and then you have people like these ... I\'d be angry but I refuse to waste my energy like that. Suffice to say I now insist on my space in the world, no more and no less, and I\'m sending you lots of good karma that the universe will deal with \"the bitches.\" Envisage a U-Haul pulling up and carting them all away -- it\'ll happen.\r\n\r\nGood luck!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060215 Firefox/3.0.11', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30', '87', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-06-23 22:38:39', '2009-06-24 02:38:39', 'It\'s okay to laugh and to mock my pain. I can take it.\r\n\r\nI am imagining a U-Haul, or a power outage local to their apartment only. If they do something more exciting I will be sure to record the evidence.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060214 Firefox/3.0.11', '', '28', '1', 'N'),
