('95', '113', 'Scott Garson', 'scgarz@gmail.com', '', '173.30.138.135', '2009-06-29 23:25:22', '2009-06-30 03:25:22', 'don\'t have any answers for you, r, but this is a great post.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_6; en-us) AppleWebKit/525.27.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/3.2.1 Safari/525.27.1', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('96', '113', 'Scott Woods', 'sewoods1@yahoo.com', 'http://scottwoods.livejournal.com/', '66.213.29.2', '2009-06-30 10:28:16', '2009-06-30 14:28:16', 'You had me at \"negroes\".\r\n\r\n- Scott \"Black writer in Ohio wondering the same thing\" Woods', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; InfoPath.1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.30)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('97', '113', 'Tim Jones-Yelvington', 'timjy@sbcglobal.net', 'http://perverseadult.blogspot.com', '173.15.104.171', '2009-06-30 11:51:14', '2009-06-30 15:51:14', 'I\'m glad you wrote this. \r\n\r\n\"When I read different online forums, itâ€™s just a bunch of white people sitting around completely uninterested in introducing race into any conversations about writing.\"\r\n\r\nYes, and I think most buy into the \"post-racial\" and \"color blind\" BS that it\'s somehow racist to talk about racism. The idea that racism is systemic instead of individual and that white supremacy is still our dominant racial system does not seem to be the way most white privileged writer folks are thinking about it. A writer once said something to me like, \"What, does racism have rules?\" And I was like, \"Um, yeah, actually, it kind of does.\" \r\n\r\nI think writers who come from any systematically marginalized identity category or community are placed in this awkward position of either having to emphasize their difference from the dominant norm (that ethnic lit model you\'re talking about contending with, sort of exoticized) or emphasize their sameness (like race, sexuality, gender, class, etc is not a factor, I\'m just a writer, and if I acknowledge difference in my work, it will somehow narrow my audience, or alienate readers) and both options kind of suck... I think the real question should always be \"different from what?\" ...we should acknowledge that we are all of us constituted by multiple differences, and privilege and oppression both come with particular sets of experiences that shape characters, and sometimes our writing will be about those things, and sometimes it will be about something else entirely.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060215 Firefox/3.0.11', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('98', '113', 'Marcelle Heath', 'marcelleheath@yahoo.com', 'http://www.offislandnovel.wordpress.com', '70.58.203.246', '2009-06-30 18:34:21', '2009-06-30 22:34:21', 'Great &amp; much needed post, Roxane. And great response, Tim. I completely agree.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X Mach-O; en-US; rv:1.8.1.20) Gecko/20081217 Firefox/2.0.0.20', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('100', '113', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-06-30 19:10:16', '2009-06-30 23:10:16', 'I don\'t have any answers either, but I did feel like just talking about this. Thanks so much for reading.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060214 Firefox/3.0.11', '', '95', '1', 'N'),
('101', '113', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-06-30 19:10:46', '2009-06-30 23:10:46', 'Scott! I know you. From LJ! Holla! I\'m going to read your submission tonight.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060214 Firefox/3.0.11', '', '96', '1', 'N'),
('102', '113', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-06-30 19:13:07', '2009-06-30 23:13:07', 'Tim, thanks for this very thoughtful reply. I agree with everything you\'ve said here. Something else I\'ve noticed in some of these forums is that we\'re so post racial that it has become okay to use racial slurs and play on stereotypes in \"ironic\" ways. Ugh. So revolting.  It\'s a huge issue, all of this race stuff, and I would love to see writers, of all races and ethnicities, talking about it productive ways--without guilt or pandering--just trying to move forward. How that\'s accomplished, I have no idea.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060214 Firefox/3.0.11', '', '97', '1', 'N'),
