('122', '130', 'david erlewine', 'daveerlewine@yahoo.com', '', '173.3.114.104', '2009-07-11 11:06:46', '2009-07-11 15:06:46', 'damn, girl, we are so much alike.  i don\'t get all the megan f hate.  she seems funny as hell to me.  the washington post called transformers 2 \"despicable\" ... apparently they weren\'t exaggerating.  i used to list a lot of stories in my bio and now i\'m shocked/embarrassed to see so many journals listed.  just annoying and so sad looking.  a lot of writers  (many of whom do great work) list A TON of journals in theirs, too, which now strikes me as weird.  so glad you said something.  ha re netflix too.  i keep closing my account then re-signing up and encountering the same fucking problem you mention.  ugh.  i am gonna go see your storyg interview.   i promised myself i wouldn\'t quit writing again until i got into storyglossia but that looks like a promise that isn\'t going to be kept.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1; GTB6; .NET CLR 1.1.4322)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('123', '130', 'erin', 'gnomeloaf@gmail.com', 'http://www.rarelylikable.com', '24.151.107.42', '2009-07-11 13:35:44', '2009-07-11 17:35:44', 'I overlist publications because I don\'t want to feel like I\'m snubbing anyone. Then I decide that\'s pretty egotistical of me, that anyone would care if I appeared to snub. It all becomes this recursive mess.\r\n\r\nRe: summer TV. Do you watch Mad Men? The last two seasons are free on demand in a lot of markets, and the new one starts next month. It makes emo look like Nickelodeon.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060215 Firefox/3.0.11 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('124', '130', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-07-11 14:38:37', '2009-07-11 18:38:37', 'It is weird when you see like 15 journals listed for more established writers. It always always baffles me. We all do it when we\'re new writers and that\'s okay.\r\n\r\nMy storyg interview will be out this week some time, to coincide with the new issue.\r\n\r\nWhy would you quit writing? Don\'t do that.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060214 Firefox/3.0.11', '', '122', '1', 'N'),
('125', '130', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-07-11 14:41:16', '2009-07-11 18:41:16', 'That makes sense.\r\n\r\nI adore Mad Men. It is such insane brilliance. I have Season 1 on DVD, and am waiting to buy season 2 this week when it is released. Joan Holloway is FIERCE. Everything about the show is fierce. And what an analogy... that it makes emo look like Nickelodeon. And so so true. Poor Betty Draper. I think I love her the most for the raging futility of her life.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060214 Firefox/3.0.11', '', '123', '1', 'N'),
('126', '130', 'david erlewine', 'daveerlewine@yahoo.com', '', '173.3.114.104', '2009-07-11 16:07:30', '2009-07-11 20:07:30', 'Betty Draper is awesome.  When that little boy (Patrick?) down the street wanted a lock of her hair...that was greatness.  \r\n\r\nMe, re writing...meh.  Who knows.  I quit for five years (as we discussed a while back) and am thinking of doing the same now.  Just too damn tiring to have these story ideas floating in my head.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1) ; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; Zune 3.0)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('127', '135', 'Ethel Rohan', 'ethelrohan@gmail.com', '', '24.4.57.196', '2009-07-12 12:10:24', '2009-07-12 16:10:24', 'Another tour de force, Roxane. What a read. I love how you twist expectations at every turn, and how much you make me feel for all of these characters, including Nora Minty. It\'s such a visceral read. This is another one of your stories that fills me with equal parts admiration for you and your work and with yearning to write stories that can take readers\' breath away.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060215 Firefox/3.0.11', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
