('16418', '205', 'Eric Beeny', 'ellipsis81@netzero.net', 'http://ericbeeny.blogspot.com', '74.78.90.7', '2009-08-13 23:22:51', '2009-08-14 03:22:51', 'I used to use loganberry for blood on the couple G.I. Joes I had. Those were the days, when death was only pretend... I always thought G.I. Joe was a recruitment tool, painting the military as honorable and decent. Also, I\'m pretty sure Celtic is the cultre and Gaelic the language, and both Irish and Scots are Celts who speak different dialects, so that\'s strange they would say \"the Celtic word.\" I didn\'t plan on seeing this movie, and I thank you for clinching it. The original cartoon movie was dope, and nothing can ever top it, except maybe the original Transformers movie from \'86, though I think they\'re both equal...', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('16419', '205', 'Ethel Rohan', 'ethelrohan@gmail.com', '', '24.4.57.196', '2009-08-14 10:17:20', '2009-08-14 14:17:20', 'Barbies are also banned in this household. Any that have ever infiltrated were promptly given to Goodwill. I hope my daughters will feel equally appreciative when they grow older, because they don\'t now e.g.: \"But whyyyyyyyyyyy?\"\r\n\r\nI am also a tough movie critic, and it never ceases to amaze me how low most movies go.\r\n\r\nEric nailed it regarding Celtic/Gaelic.\r\n \r\nThanks for a terrific post: fun and intelligent.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US) AppleWebKit/530.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/2.0.172.39 Safari/530.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('16464', '205', 'Ben White', 'benjamin.white@post.harvard.edu', 'http://benwhite.com', '70.124.126.170', '2009-08-14 15:35:38', '2009-08-14 19:35:38', 'Correct me if I\'m wrong, but I <em>believe</em> the reason these hollow shells of pseudo-humanity insist on ruining everything holy from our childhood is that they market test the shit out of everything until its stripped of anything resembling a soul. Their audience (Busch-lite drinking man-boys and their explosion-seeking children) will pay for movies as long as they are ensured a certain ratio of explosions/fighting to talking and hot women to plot. The fact that the studios can save money by using CGI instead of actual talent and pyrotechnics is only a bonus.\r\n\r\nOn a side note, I laughed out loud several times while reading this review, and my wife got very suspicious.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.13) Gecko/2009073022 Firefox/3.0.13 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729) AutoPager/0.5.2.2 (http://www.teesoft.info/)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('16727', '205', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-08-15 23:22:39', '2009-08-16 03:22:39', 'Eric that is so awesome that you got real with the blood. Nice. Thank you for the clarification re Gaelic and Celtic. I thought the whole thing was suspect. It seems much like Oriental (things) versus Asian (people).  If you have any fondness for GI Joe, don\'t see the movie. Unless you\'re very sad and need a good laugh.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.1) Gecko/2008070206 Firefox/3.0.1', '', '16418', '1', 'N'),
('16728', '205', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-08-15 23:24:38', '2009-08-16 03:24:38', 'I didn\'t understand the Barbie thing as a young girl. I cried over it and then I realized I could play with most anything else and then I realized that Barbie was stupid because she didn\'t fit well in the GI Joe vehicles. I am shocked by the way movies are sinking into a cesspool of suck. Its not that I expect better of Hollywood. I don\'t. But I expect more from humanity and that\'s why it hurts so much. Hee!\r\n\r\nGlad to know I wasn\'t crazy about the Gaelic/Celtic distinction. \r\n\r\nYou\'re welcome. Thanks for reading!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.1) Gecko/2008070206 Firefox/3.0.1', '', '16419', '1', 'N'),
('16729', '205', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-08-15 23:26:26', '2009-08-16 03:26:26', 'Test marketing definitely holds a lot of the blame here. That\'s a real shame. You can\'t test for taste, clearly. The weird thing is that CGI can be super expensive. I don\'t understand the rational for its excessive use in this movie. \r\n\r\nThat\'s funny that this post drew suspicious looks. You must have been laughing the way I laughed in the theatre.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.1) Gecko/2008070206 Firefox/3.0.1', '', '16464', '1', 'N'),
