('30113', '262', 'Erin', 'gnomeloaf@gmail.com', 'http://www.rarelylikable.com', '24.177.85.170', '2009-09-10 09:26:08', '2009-09-10 13:26:08', 'I want to hate Garth Brooks, in the way that I want to hate a lot of country music artists. But then I remember the episode of Saturday Night Live where he was Coco the Old French Whore -- and how he seemed sweet and endearing, and all is forgiven. I can\'t find a video of the sketch on the Internet, and it\'s really bumming me out.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.9.1.2) Gecko/20090729 Firefox/3.5.2 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30114', '262', 'paula', 'pbomrock@yahoo.com', 'http://www.paulabomer.com', '24.193.52.22', '2009-09-10 10:41:40', '2009-09-10 14:41:40', 'Hey girl (haha),\r\nOn the one hand, I really feel for you because people are stupid and annoying. But I also feel sorry for that guy who brought up soul food. Why? Because he was trying to be nice. Now, he made a jackass of himself, but he wasn\'t like \"I don\'t want to talk to this woman because she\'s black\" which, because this world is so fucked up and racism is a reality, is what another person might think/do. My kids went to a public school for five years in Brooklyn where they were either the only white kid, or one of two or three in their classrooms. I don\'t even know where to begin with the endless crap they got. This is not to say that thier entire lives will not be easier until they die because they are white- their lives will be easier beyond belief. \r\n\r\nOn a lighter note, do you remember that website (I think, right?) that posted anon questions that blacks had for whites and visa versa? I thought it was genuis. It just showed that people DON\'T KNOW. It was funny, too. My favorite one was \"why do white people smell like wet dogs?\" it was just a genuine question, you know?', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 6.0; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; InfoPath.2; .NET CLR 3.5.21022; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30618; MS-RTC LM 8)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30115', '262', 'Ethel Rohan', 'ethelrohan@gmail.com', '', '24.4.57.196', '2009-09-10 11:00:37', '2009-09-10 15:00:37', 'I love your subtitle \"blah, blah, blah and shiny.\"\r\n\r\nI\'m sorry you\'re tired and riled-up, but thanks for sharing. You reminded me of an exchange I had with one of our neighbors. She said on first meeting me \"oh we\'ve tons of Irish nannies and cleaners working in the neighborhood, you girls make the best help.\" A couple of years later, and I\'m still not sure what to do with that comment, but I err on the side of laughter. I know she thought she was being nice too!\r\n\r\nHang in there, the acceptances will come. You have the Midas touch remember.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US) AppleWebKit/530.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/2.0.172.43 Safari/530.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30116', '254', 'david e', 'daveerlewine@yahoo.com', '', '206.138.130.2', '2009-09-10 11:27:58', '2009-09-10 15:27:58', 'Roxane, that is such a great way to say it.  I get overwhelmed (mainly in good ways) when I encounter so many wonderful online journals.  I really hope to make it into Staccato at some point.  I\'ve loved everything I\'ve read there so far.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '30102', '0', 'N'),
