('30226', '281', 'ryan', 'rwrkb@hotmail.com', 'http://ryanwbradley.blogspot.com', '209.180.234.212', '2009-09-25 13:24:02', '2009-09-25 17:24:02', 'i agree.\r\n\r\nand on top of all that, i think if an editor is going to reject my piece because i queried after 200 days then chances are they weren\'t going to publish it anyway, and if they were they shouldn\'t have been. editors should publish work they love, if me wanting to know what\'s up is enough to sway their feelings then my story or poem wasn\'t good enough.\r\n\r\nall that said, i\'ve dealt with a few very gracious editors, who after losing hundred of poems when my hard drive died were kind enough to forward my submissions back to me so that i could still have them, even though their publications weren\'t going to use them.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.14) Gecko/2009082707 Firefox/3.0.14', '', '30224', '0', 'N'),
