('30120', '262', 'ryan', 'rwrkb@hotmail.com', 'http://ryanwbradley.blogspot.com', '63.224.202.134', '2009-09-10 15:57:08', '2009-09-10 19:57:08', 'gawd, duotrope totally gives false hope. like \"shit their acceptances have a 78 day avg and their rejections have a 22 day avg and they\'ve had my story for 79 days, i\'m so in!\" and then on day 80 you get a rejection, haha. i just had one of those bubble bursts yesterday. oh well. 27 stories still out, and around the same number of poems. it\'s the submission machine, rejection in, submission out.\r\n\r\nyour post reminded me of a scene in some movie where a bunch of suits are meeting and this guy is shaking all their hands and he gets to a black businessman and instead of shaking his hand he goes to give him a fist bump.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.13) Gecko/2009073022 Firefox/3.0.13', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
