('30122', '262', 'Angi', 'angi.becker.stevens@gmail.com', 'http://angibeckerstevens.blogspot.com', '69.14.150.65', '2009-09-10 20:25:22', '2009-09-11 00:25:22', 'It\'s really, really frustrating how many idiotic, ignorant white people there are in the world. Obviously that kind of stupidity is a whole lot better than outright bigotry, but that doesn\'t make it even remotely okay. I just don\'t even know where people get the idea that it\'s reasonable or acceptable to act like that. \r\n\r\nI just ordered the new Lorrie Moore and am super excited. I\'ve read everything of hers except Anagrams. Also, I\'m slowly reading Scorch Atlas (I\'ve had it for quite a while) and I like it but I feel like I need to take the post-apocalyptic stuff in small doses. Why did you not want to love it?\r\n\r\nI used to watch GH years ago and it amuses me how many names are still the same.\r\n\r\nAlso, damn Duotrope: strongly agree. They are so anxiety inducing.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060214 Firefox/3.0.11', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
