('30124', '262', 'david e', 'daveerlewine@yahoo.com', '', '206.138.130.2', '2009-09-11 07:02:10', '2009-09-11 11:02:10', 'Never in a million years would I call any woman \"girl\".  I don\'t even call my 19-month old daughter that. \r\n\r\nMy wife is Vietnamese.  It\'s amazing how many times people ask her, \"What are you?\"  \r\n\r\nDuotrope continues to haunt me.  I love it so much one day and am swearing it off the next day.  Like everything else, my dad\'s motto \"moderation is key\" should guide me.  It doesn\'t/won\'t.  \r\n\r\nAnd, I agree with Ethel:  Roxane, you do have the Midas touch.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
