('30239', '281', 'Ben White', 'benjamin.white@post.harvard.edu', 'http://benwhite.com', '70.124.126.170', '2009-09-28 15:59:19', '2009-09-28 19:59:19', 'I never thought I would query, but recently I realized that a publication put out its issue that I had submitted for (and hadn\'t rejected me), so I email to let them know, figuring that I might not be the only one whose rejection slipped through. More of a heads up. Nanoism\'s duotrope records shows a few non-responses, and it was news to me. I\'d prefer to think that I\'d answer everything sent my way.\r\n\r\nSo anyway, I got an email back, saying \"our bad\" and both short pieces were accepted for a future issue. I\'m still shocked and wouldn\'t be surprised it was a practical joke. But it does make me question the acceptance as some sort of guilt-induced kindness, and that makes me a little sad.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '30209', '0', 'N'),
