('30150', '265', 'robert', 'robert@robertswartwood.com', 'http://www.robertswartwood.com', '24.152.219.224', '2009-09-14 13:39:40', '2009-09-14 17:39:40', 'I have an issue with Quick Fiction, besides the self-pampering form rejection. I only submitted once, and in the mail (because they got my postal address) I received a letter asking for donations. The letter talked about how you can donate from as little as $1 to $10 and if you donate between $500 and $1,000 you can become a kind of \"member\" or whatever. So I thought: Okay, if this place is getting donations of that amount, why are they still not paying their writers? Even five, ten, twenty bucks? I e-mailed them the question and got back a response that if I donate to make a note the donation is for the writers, that the writers would much appreciate it. Is it just me or does that sound wrong?', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30151', '265', 'Jason Jordan', 'circus_brimstone@yahoo.com', 'http://poweringthedevilscircus.blogspot.com', '74.129.199.18', '2009-09-14 14:09:47', '2009-09-14 18:09:47', 'Cool. Thanks!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US) AppleWebKit/530.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/2.0.172.43 Safari/530.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30152', '265', 'ryan', 'rwrkb@hotmail.com', 'http://ryanwbradley.blogspot.com', '63.224.202.134', '2009-09-14 14:15:26', '2009-09-14 18:15:26', 'pretty much every story i write under 500 words gets sent to Quick Fiction first. i like their style. i want to be in with the in crowd. still haven\'t cracked that nut. will continue to bug them until they accept me or close up shop so as not to have to deal with me.\r\n\r\nre: those kinds of rejections, they always remind me of the brush offs i got from girls in high school.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.14) Gecko/2009082707 Firefox/3.0.14', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30244', '293', 'Sean', 'leapsloth14@hotmail.com', 'http://seanlovelace.com', '98.227.19.35', '2009-09-29 22:33:07', '2009-09-30 02:33:07', 'WTF?\r\n\r\nYou should call out anyone who fucks up your name. Come on. Anyway, I fixed that. Fuck. Never let people fuck around with your name. It\'s your NAME.\r\n\r\nS', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30245', '293', 'Sean', 'leapsloth14@hotmail.com', 'http://seanlovelace.com', '98.227.19.35', '2009-09-29 22:33:41', '2009-09-30 02:33:41', 'I was called \"seen\" for years so maybe sensitive?\r\n\r\nS', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30246', '293', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '141.219.213.246', '2009-09-29 22:42:35', '2009-09-30 02:42:35', 'I\'m super sensitive about it but its such a losing battle. I can sign my name in an e-mail spelled correctly and people write back misspelling my name. I pick my battles and after 8 pm, I give up the ghost! Thanks for fixing the spelling of my name!\r\n\r\nSeen? Wow.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '30245', '1', 'N'),
('30155', '268', 'gaydegani', 'gaydegani@yahoo.com', '', '198.161.31.12', '2009-09-14 23:38:55', '2009-09-15 03:38:55', 'Love \"How It is.\"  The ending especially.  Nice. Nice.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; GTB5; .NET CLR 1.1.4322)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30156', '262', 'Joseph Young', 'youngjoseph21@hotmail.com', 'http://www.verysmalldogs.blogspot.com', '71.179.220.133', '2009-09-15 00:09:59', '2009-09-15 04:09:59', 'hey, roxane. i liked your rule piece on vip vsf a lot.\r\n\r\ndavid--i call my women friends \'girl\' a lot. not black friends, all of them. i think it\'s a really sweet thing. i like when they call me boy too. it\'s nice, sweet. i can understand the reluctance to use the term though.\r\n\r\nroxane--so many white people i know are uncomfortable around black people. they get really nervous. it\'s unfamiliarity. not that it\'s an excuse for some of the strange things you report here. but it\'s strange. it\'s strange that it\'s so common still, that unfamiliarity. \r\n\r\nnice blog. glad to have stumbled onto it.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 6.0; WOW64; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; Media Center PC 5.0; .NET CLR 3.5.21022; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30618; MDDC)', '', '30124', '0', 'N'),
('30249', '293', 'Eric Beeny', 'ellipsis81@netzero.net', 'http://ericbeeny.blogspot.com', '74.78.90.7', '2009-09-30 22:06:49', '2009-10-01 02:06:49', 'Hi, Roxane. I\'m big digging both your stories. Keep it up...', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30158', '265', 'david e', 'daveerlewine@yahoo.com', 'http://www.whizbyfiction.blogspot.com/', '206.138.130.2', '2009-09-15 09:33:55', '2009-09-15 13:33:55', 'Ha, I had the same question!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '30149', '0', 'N'),
('30159', '265', 'david e', 'daveerlewine@yahoo.com', 'http://www.whizbyfiction.blogspot.com/', '206.138.130.2', '2009-09-15 09:36:06', '2009-09-15 13:36:06', 'well said, all around, ryan.  i saw on duotrope that william walsh (great story in PANK now) just got an accept from Quick Fiction.  \r\n\r\ni love their stuff.  Definitely, rejections like that remind me of high school, college, law school, and the, uh, real world.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '30152', '0', 'N'),
('30160', '268', 'david e', 'daveerlewine@yahoo.com', 'http://www.whizbyfiction.blogspot.com/', '206.138.130.2', '2009-09-15 09:42:33', '2009-09-15 13:42:33', 'Oh, wow, I love this.  Don\'t think I don\'t notice the shout to your \"best friend\" Ryan.  Laura Ellen Scott has a story up on F-aut with a \"David\" narrator.  I hope you can follow suit some time.  \r\n\r\nYou nailed the backstory...making us wait to find out what happened in high school but not too long.  I agree with Gay...the ending is just wonderful.  The image of Ryan standing guard at the house is superb.  I also loved the image of the crying son/brother making a mess of the situation.  \r\n\r\nWell done.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30247', '293', 'paula', 'pbomrock@yahoo.com', 'http://www.paulabomer.com', '24.193.55.191', '2009-09-30 17:51:02', '2009-09-30 21:51:02', 'I get \"Boner\" - pretty much non-stop. The occasional \"Boomer\". I\'m OK- it\'s so \"unconscious\"- I never take it personally.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 6.0; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; InfoPath.2; .NET CLR 3.5.21022; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30618; MS-RTC LM 8)', '', '30246', '0', 'N'),
