('30163', '268', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-09-15 17:12:15', '2009-09-15 21:12:15', 'Dave, ha! I\'ll do my best. Glad you enjoyed this.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '30160', '1', 'N'),
('30164', '265', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-09-15 17:13:51', '2009-09-15 21:13:51', 'Robert, that does sound strange, but I have to believe few if any people have ever taken them up on that offer. Perhaps by \"for the writers\" they mean that the money subsidizes printing costs, but I cannot speak for them, I do not know. I do not enjoy being hit up for solicitations for magazines though. I understand why you are put off.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '30150', '1', 'N'),
('30165', '265', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-09-15 17:14:37', '2009-09-15 21:14:37', 'Ryan, this was my first time submitting to them. I\'ll try again. I\'d love to be amongst the cool kids they publish.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '30152', '1', 'N'),
('30166', '262', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '71.13.217.52', '2009-09-15 17:16:52', '2009-09-15 21:16:52', 'Hi Joseph,\r\n\r\nThanks for your comment. I understand that white people might be uncomfortable around black people but you know, the same holds true, and also, we\'re not that different so the notion of unfamiliarity troubles me a bit. It\'s not like we\'re talking about a different species here. Still, I understand what you\'re saying no matter how much it frustrates me. Glad you\'re enjoying the blog!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '30156', '1', 'N'),
('30167', '265', 'Angi', 'angi.becker.stevens@gmail.com', 'http://angibeckerstevens.blogspot.com', '69.14.150.65', '2009-09-15 18:02:45', '2009-09-15 22:02:45', 'I just got that rejection from Quick Fiction a few weeks ago, too. It was only my second time submitting to them.\r\n\r\nI\'ve had something languishing with Copper Nickel for a long time, too. Juked did that to me, too, for the print edition. They\'d had the piece way past their average, so I finally wrote and inquired, was told it was still under consideration, and then eventually got a form rejection. Damn Duotrope for making us obsess!\r\n\r\nI already said this on facebook, but I love the Wigleaf story!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.11) Gecko/2009060214 Firefox/3.0.11', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
