('30208', '281', 'david erlewine', 'daveerlewine@yahoo.com', 'http://www.whizbyfiction.blogspot.com/', '68.33.40.219', '2009-09-24 21:40:55', '2009-09-25 01:40:55', 'ryan\'s story is another reason i avoid mailing out subs anymore.  ugh, i haven\'t done that since i started writing again in november 08.  is there any reason why journals can\'t just get online sub managers and call it a day?  at what point will all journals give up the ghost and do that?  by 2013?  will any journals then still be talking about SASEs?', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 6.0; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; MDDC; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30618)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30209', '281', 'Matt Bell', 'mdbell79@gmail.com', 'http://www.mdbell.com', '76.204.6.204', '2009-09-25 00:38:27', '2009-09-25 04:38:27', 'I can\'t remember having ever queried a magazine, except to follow up on a solicitation (which feels different, somehow-- partly because when I sent someone something for a solicitation, I generally send it nowhere else until I hear back from them, if possible.) \r\n\r\nI don\'t query because I don\'t know anyone who has done it and then gotten an acceptance. I assume it happens, but I\'ll bet it doesn\'t happen very often, because the easiest way to get rid of the querying party is to reject them immediately.  I say be patient, or move on. If you\'re going to send a query, you might as well send a withdrawal instead. It\'s less painful, and then you can submit again soon without that query in between you and the editor.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30210', '279', 'Kirsty Logan', 'hello@kirstylogan.com', 'http://www.kirstylogan.com', '94.195.140.126', '2009-09-25 03:09:55', '2009-09-25 07:09:55', 'I sent a story to Electric Literature 56 days ago, and soon it\'s going to turn red in my Duotrope submissions tracker. Looks like I\'ve got another month to wait...', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30214', '281', 'Laura Ellen Scott', 'lscott18@verizon.net', 'http://probablyjustastory.blogspot.com/', '96.231.17.21', '2009-09-25 07:27:47', '2009-09-25 11:27:47', 'I think Matt\'s completely right, although I have no plans to withdraw my June 2008 sub to 42opus because I have this fantasy that leaving it in their automated system helps to dirty it up. \r\n\r\nLoved the Catalonian story, really tight and elegant and icky. The link in your post is wrong, though.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
