('30220', '281', 'Sheldon Lee Compton', 'sheldoncompton@yahoo.com', 'http://www.wrongtreereview.com', '72.147.17.104', '2009-09-25 10:42:46', '2009-09-25 14:42:46', 'I have six stories that have been out 150 days plus and figure, like Matt said, if I write and ask anything the whole deal will go from mysterious to somehow bad.  As an editor, I\'ve fielded a few of my own for both Cellar Door and Wrong Tree but thinking back, I\'m sure I deserved it.  And, yeah, SASE are four letters I would love to never see cuddling up again.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X Mach-O; en-US; rv:1.8.1.20) Gecko/20081217 Firefox/2.0.0.20', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30275', '307', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '24.247.41.152', '2009-10-10 18:43:49', '2009-10-10 22:43:49', 'Haha. Glad you liked it, Laura!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '30269', '0', 'N'),
('30223', '281', 'ryan', 'rwrkb@hotmail.com', 'http://ryanwbradley.blogspot.com', '71.215.183.192', '2009-09-25 11:56:49', '2009-09-25 15:56:49', 'i have 11 that have been out over 240 days... 3 of those have been out over a year. i\'ve queried four of those 11 and never heard back from any. all four have a notes in their guidelines saying to query after either 90 days or 6 months.\r\n\r\ni will probably never query again, but i also won\'t feel guilty sending those stories to other markets.\r\n\r\ni guess i was ingrained with an old school attitude toward this stuff. i\'ve heard some editors from pretty big journals say \"yes, query us if we are taking a long time, you deserve to know if we got it or lost it or are just taking our time.\" \r\n\r\nmy attitude toward a lot of this stuff is becoming \"eh\" i\'ll just write my shit and send it out and then send it out again, thinking about the rest of it is just too much work for an unproductive cause.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '30220', '0', 'N'),
('30224', '281', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '141.219.214.55', '2009-09-25 12:02:22', '2009-09-25 16:02:22', 'I don\'t mind being queried as an editor. Sometimes things fall through the cracks. I don\'t mind querying as a writer either. I do it very sparingly but sometimes, I need closure and if editors don\'t like being queried they should state, explicitly to not query. As Ryan said, when you say query after 4 months, and it\'s been 15, I\'m going to query and if that query irritates you enough to reject my story prematurely, I\'m comfortable with that too. I\'m the kind of person who has to know, one way or the other. It\'s in my DNA or something.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '0', '1', 'N'),
