('30362', '346', 'Steven Tweddell', 'rstweddell1@hotmail.com', '', '74.86.186.80', '2009-11-08 01:16:02', '2009-11-08 05:16:02', 'Roxanne,\r\n\r\nI donâ€™t know what just happened. If you end up getting two comments from me Iâ€™m sorry. I just read â€œLa Negra Blancaâ€ in the Collagist. It was great. It made me jealous that I didnâ€™t write something like that. Only, I couldnâ€™t write something like that at this point in my life. Maybe one day. Maybe never. \r\n\r\nI, too, am going through a trying period of rejection after rejection. Quickly heading toward 200, maybe more. But then, Iâ€™ve been working on that number for twelve years now. I have published a story in a pretty credible journal, North American Review, but it hasnâ€™t given me the street cred I had hoped. I also won a grant early this year, something I thought was pretty amazing. But I donâ€™t know if thatâ€™s getting me closer reads or not because the form rejections seem to come just as often as before. \r\n\r\nIâ€™m living in Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates, right now. We came here because my wife got a job teaching English in the public schools. Right now, Iâ€™m jobless, looking for work in the Middle East. Iâ€™m so tired of working shitty jobs that Iâ€™ve kind of told myself Iâ€™m just going to write for a living even if I have to write hack work to get by. So far, I havenâ€™t picked up any work. I just started looking last week, though. In the meantime, Iâ€™m going to keep writing fiction and, I hope, more essays and journalism and lists and letters to the editor or what have you. How much does it cost to keep up your website? \r\n\r\nGood luck. You deserve it. I just read another blog entry from http://wardsix.blogspot.com/. October 18, 2009. I think itâ€™s pertinent to your latest entry. I hope you enjoy. \r\n\r\nSteven Tweddell', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.9.1.5) Gecko/20091102 Firefox/3.5.5 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30363', '346', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '24.247.41.152', '2009-11-08 04:04:34', '2009-11-08 08:04:34', 'Thanks for your comment Steven and I\'m glad you enjoyed La Negra Blanca. Rejection is so tough. That\'s why I talk about it. The North American Review is an amazing journal but in my experience the only cred that matters when you\'re not a big name is the quality of the work you\'re submitting. You should definitely keep writing. My website costs about 100/year, very affordable. I actually read the Ward Six entry you mention, and it is indeed very interesting and pertinent to my lament here.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '30362', '1', 'N'),
('30364', '346', 'Brad Green', 'glberen@gmail.com', 'http://elevatetheordinary.blogspot.com', '207.43.79.15', '2009-11-08 10:09:49', '2009-11-08 14:09:49', 'When one loses direction, just plow forward.  Often causes me to have a sore head, but at least I\'m moving.  When one is moving, one is not directionless.  \r\n\r\nNext week you\'ll write a post about some spectacular acceptance you just received or the press that read your post and asked to see your collections.  Just you wait.  You\'ll see.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.5) Gecko/20091102 Firefox/3.5.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30365', '346', 'Tim Jones-Yelvington', 'timjy@sbcglobal.net', 'http://perverseadult.blogspot.com', '75.22.18.247', '2009-11-08 13:10:12', '2009-11-08 17:10:12', 'I want to school with Diane Goettel from Black Lawrence. I can kick her in the shins for you. Ayiti sounds great... what abt City Lights?', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.3) Gecko/20090824 Firefox/3.5.3', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30366', '346', 'Paula Ray', 'PaulaRayABC@aol.com', 'http://musicalpencil.blogspot.com./', '174.106.73.120', '2009-11-08 13:56:22', '2009-11-08 17:56:22', 'Hi Roxanne,\r\n\r\nI\'ve not had the pleasure of meeting you, but I\'ve read many of your stories and have even checked out your blog several times. \r\n\r\nI think it is wonderful that one your collections is \"ethnic\" and has a specific theme. You may feel frustrated searching for the right home for it, but look at it this way, when you do find the market that truly appreciates the work - they will most likely promote it whole-heartedly and it will definitely stand out in the crowd. The collection that is harder to place may also be the collection that has the most original voice and isn\'t easily pigeon-holed.\r\n\r\nI wish you luck placing it and the other more mainstream collection. \r\n\r\nYou mention you feel down sometimes, because of the frequency of rejections you receive, but I\'ve seen your name on Duotrope so often for acceptances - you are a celebrity in my eyes. I dare say you\'ve received more acceptances in the past six months than many writers have received in six years. You are doing fantastic!\r\n\r\nI\'m a fan.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nPaula', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.0; Trident/4.0; GTB6; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; Media Center PC 5.1; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30618)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30367', '346', 'Helen W. Mallon', 'hmallon@navpoint.com', 'http://hmallon-ftheeiwasateenagequaker.blogspot.com/', '71.23.194.187', '2009-11-08 14:11:29', '2009-11-08 18:11:29', 'Hi, Roxane,\r\n\r\nI\'m new to your website.  It\'s a brutal business, submitting our writing.  This may make you laugh:  I once did a several-submissions-back-and-forth correspondence thing with an editor thru several rounds of my poems. I decided that #5 would be my last.  \r\n\r\nI\'ll always keep the letter he wrote back: \"The problem here lies not in the technique but rather the tenor.  As an editor I have made it my position to publish only work that indicates in some way that life is worth living, that existence is a positive process.  These writings of yours that I\'ve seen do not...etc...\"\r\n\r\nI can be grateful, I guess, that readers were spared.  !??\r\n\r\nAlso, this: In graduate school one professor did a talk called \"embracing rejection.\" He has saved every rejection slip he\'s ever received.  He was repeatedly rejected by one journal, which, after several years, turned around and asked him to become the Editor. \r\n\r\nIt\'s a whacky process.  Sucky, but inot without humor.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.0; Trident/4.0; GTB6.3; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; Media Center PC 5.0; .NET CLR 3.5.21022; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30618)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30368', '346', 'ryan', 'rwrkb@hotmail.com', 'http://ryanwbradley.blogspot.com', '71.210.28.81', '2009-11-08 14:30:55', '2009-11-08 18:30:55', 'i got my la review rejection yesterday, too. it must be rejection season again. i\'ve garnered eight in the last four days.\r\n\r\nand i feel your pain about not knowing where to send stuff. i have a novel that\'s still out to about a dozen places. but i have a couple weird novellas that i have no clue where to send. every place i want to send them isn\'t accepting unsolicited manuscripts. \r\n\r\nfun, this writing thing. :)', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.5) Gecko/20091102 Firefox/3.5.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30370', '346', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '24.247.41.152', '2009-11-10 17:12:04', '2009-11-10 21:12:04', 'Hi Yvette,\r\n\r\nI actually own this book. It is amazing. I\'m definitely going to enter the UIowa contest next year.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.4) Gecko/20091016 Firefox/3.5.4', '', '30369', '0', 'N'),
('30528', '355', 'ryan', 'rwrkb@hotmail.com', 'http://ryanwbradley.blogspot.com', '71.34.241.71', '2009-11-27 16:58:57', '2009-11-27 20:58:57', 'the editor of zyzzyva commented on lauren becker\'s blog recently, too!\r\n\r\nand, david, i think i black out with my rejections, too. my wife can even spot the one\'s that come in the mail, she texts me at work to tell me i got a rejection, then i can blackout at work', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.15) Gecko/2009101601 Firefox/3.0.15', '', '30518', '0', 'N'),
('30746', '396', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '24.247.41.152', '2009-12-15 15:30:47', '2009-12-15 19:30:47', 'I will be in Philly 12/26-12/30 interviewing at MLA so I won\'t have a lot of free time. I will be able to visit NYC when I\'m on the east coast in February.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.5) Gecko/20091102 Firefox/3.5.5', '', '30745', '1', 'N'),
('30552', '359', 'Gay Degani', 'gaydegani@yahoo.com', 'http://www.gaydegani.com', '99.66.207.49', '2009-11-30 02:17:26', '2009-11-30 06:17:26', '\"I feel like the work I have circulating is some of my strongest writing and yet I am meeting with rejection constantly so perhaps the writing isnâ€™t as strong as I thought? Crisis.\"\r\n\r\nI\'m certain--absolutely certain--what you have out there is as strong as you think.  Believe in it.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; GTB6; SU 3.24; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30556', '359', 'Eric Beeny', 'ellipsis81@netzero.net', 'http://ericbeeny.blogspot.com', '74.78.90.7', '2009-11-30 09:20:26', '2009-11-30 13:20:26', 'That\'s crazy-bananas, and I\'ve received several of those paper rejections, too, how far away the impersonal note is from the journal\'s address (the journal\'s \'identity\'), as if they\'re not only distancing themselves from the submitting author, but completely dissociating themselves from their own decision about the author\'s work, almost refusing to take responsibility, maybe...', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30750', '396', 'EC', 'bronterre@earthlink.net', 'http://thechagallposition.blogspot.com/', '71.192.163.91', '2009-12-15 18:42:14', '2009-12-15 22:42:14', 'I\'m with Brad Green, I appreciate the quick response times (but I figured that every writer did, so what do I know?).\r\n\r\nAnd I, too, am weary of the obligatory year-end (and now decade-end) flurry of \"listurbation.\"', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.21.8 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.4 Safari/531.21.10', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30973', '432', 'Yvette', 'writer@yswconsulting.com', 'http://yvettewardhorner.blogspot.com', '75.165.220.8', '2010-01-14 18:40:29', '2010-01-14 22:40:29', 'I saw some footage of this yesterday and it was unspeakable. I\'m so glad your parents weren\'t there and I hope your missing relatives show up unharmed.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1) ; .NET CLR 1.0.3705; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; Media Center PC 4.0; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30561', '359', 'ryan', 'rwrkb@hotmail.com', 'http://ryanwbradley.blogspot.com', '71.34.241.71', '2009-11-30 16:48:09', '2009-11-30 20:48:09', 'roxane, i feel the same way about the work i have out. we must keep believing!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.15) Gecko/2009101601 Firefox/3.0.15', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30383', '346', 'Helen W. Mallon', 'hmallon@navpoint.com', 'http://hmallon-ftheeiwasateenagequaker.blogspot.com/', '71.23.194.187', '2009-11-15 15:07:08', '2009-11-15 19:07:08', 'Hi, Roxane,\r\n\r\nI printed out and read La Negra Blanca...wow.  I\'d like to use this story in a CW class I hope to teach next semester. \r\n\r\nKeep the faith!!!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.0; Trident/4.0; GTB6.3; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; Media Center PC 5.0; .NET CLR 3.5.21022; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30618)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30562', '359', 'davidpeak', 'rubberpalmtrees@yahoo.com', 'http://davidpeak.blogspot.com', '38.112.3.162', '2009-11-30 17:48:51', '2009-11-30 21:48:51', 'i would like more stories about the places in your town and the town across the bridge, please. the laundromat rundown was great. you know, not necessarily exploitative, more exploratory. really, just great.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.15) Gecko/2009101601 Firefox/3.0.15 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729) WinNT-PAI 09.09.2009', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30387', '346', 'Sarah Layden', 'calmoots@yahoo.com', 'http://www.sarahlayden.com', '65.29.92.118', '2009-11-15 19:58:03', '2009-11-15 23:58:03', 'Hi Roxane,\r\nKeep at it. Rejection\'s par for this field\'s course, and I see your work everywhere -- really, it\'s impressive! And rare, in case you don\'t know. \r\n\r\nTake care,\r\nSL', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.15) Gecko/2009101601 Firefox/3.0.15 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30393', '346', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '24.247.41.152', '2009-11-16 02:48:32', '2009-11-16 06:48:32', 'HI Paula,\r\n\r\nThanks so much for your kind response and offering much-needed perspective. I am quite blessed as a writer and I do need to remember that even during these interminable spans of rejection. My best to you!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.4) Gecko/20091016 Firefox/3.5.4', '', '30366', '0', 'N'),
('30394', '346', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '24.247.41.152', '2009-11-16 02:51:05', '2009-11-16 06:51:05', 'Hi Helen,\r\n\r\nThanks so much for your note. I am learning to accept/embrace rejection. More often than not, I try to use it productively, finding ways to improve my work but then there are those bad spells such as the one in which I am currently mired and then I lose sight of the benefits of rejection. Glad you want to use La Negra Blanca in your class. I am truly honored.\r\n\r\nI can\'t but I can believe the story of your back and forth with the editor who only wanted to send hope and light into the world. I fear he would find all of my writing inappropriate. As you say, it is likely for the best!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.4) Gecko/20091016 Firefox/3.5.4', '', '30367', '0', 'N'),
('30395', '346', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '24.247.41.152', '2009-11-16 02:51:43', '2009-11-16 06:51:43', 'It is definitely rejection season. I\'m pretty damn over it.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.4) Gecko/20091016 Firefox/3.5.4', '', '30368', '0', 'N'),
('30396', '346', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '24.247.41.152', '2009-11-16 02:52:09', '2009-11-16 06:52:09', 'Hi Sarah. Thanks for the perspective. You take care too!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.4) Gecko/20091016 Firefox/3.5.4', '', '30387', '0', 'N'),
('30856', '420', 'Kirsty Logan', 'hello@kirstylogan.com', 'http://www.kirstylogan.com', '94.195.140.126', '2009-12-31 08:07:16', '2009-12-31 12:07:16', 'This is such an inspiring post. I can\'t believe how much you\'ve achieved in one year: I don\'t know whether to be murderously jealous or happy for you. A bit of both.\r\n\r\nOn a side note, I am honoured to be part of PANK\'s next issue. That story, The Rental Heart, had been rejected a bunch of times but I had a real soft spot for it so I kept sending it out. So glad I did now! I can\'t wait to see the issue.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.6) Gecko/20091201 Firefox/3.5.6', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30400', '346', 'Kirsty Logan', 'hello@kirstylogan.com', 'http://www.fracturedwest.com', '94.195.140.126', '2009-11-16 04:33:14', '2009-11-16 08:33:14', 'This doesn\'t really help your publisher hunt, but I like this post as I am very interested in:\r\na. your writing, and\r\nb. Haiti;\r\nso I\'d love to see these two things combined. If you do find a publisher then I\'ll be buying the book. Are any of the stories available online?', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.5) Gecko/20091102 Firefox/3.5.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30401', '346', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '24.247.41.152', '2009-11-16 04:47:52', '2009-11-16 08:47:52', 'Hi Kirsty,\r\n\r\nA couple of the stories are available online. Motherfuckers is at decomp: http://www.decompmagazine.com/motherfuckers.htm and Things I Know About Fairytales is at Necessary Fiction http://necessaryfiction.com/2009/05/things-i-know-about-fairy-tales.html. Another story is in the print magazine Weave and the rest are making the rounds. \r\n\r\nIf and when I place this manuscript, I will let you know!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.4) Gecko/20091016 Firefox/3.5.4', '', '30400', '1', 'N'),
('30406', '349', 'ryan', 'rwrkb@hotmail.com', 'http://ryanwbradley.blogspot.com', '71.210.28.81', '2009-11-16 12:45:14', '2009-11-16 16:45:14', 'i\'ve had stuff i withdrew rejected before, it always makes me laugh. but my favorite was that i queried a journal a couple years ago, because it had been nearly a year. they told me they never received a submission from me and i was \"d\'oh\" then a month later i got a rejection letter from them.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.5) Gecko/20091102 Firefox/3.5.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30570', '355', 'Tim Jones-Yelvington', 'timjy@sbcglobal.net', 'http://perverseadult.blogspot.com', '173.15.104.171', '2009-12-01 13:37:16', '2009-12-01 17:37:16', 'I\'m all about magazines encouraging folks to subscribe, but that whole bit of sending the subscription pitch at the same time as the rejection sort of seems like a bad call, strategically speaking. The folks at Shenandoah send their subscription pitch separately from their rejection, which I thought was really classy and also very wise re: fundraising strategy. Their rejection slip is also very elegantly-worded and in general left me with a very positive impression.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.5) Gecko/20091102 Firefox/3.5.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30869', '420', 'paula', 'pbomrock@yahoo.com', 'http://www.paulabomer.com', '69.128.229.68', '2009-12-31 22:57:57', '2010-01-01 02:57:57', 'One of the best things to happen to me in 2009 was to get to know you, Roxane. I really look forward to continuing our friendship in 2010- come to NYC and visit me in Feb!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 6.0; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; InfoPath.2; .NET CLR 3.5.21022; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30618; MS-RTC LM 8) chromeframe/4.0', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30415', '349', 'MoGa', 'molly.gaudry@gmail.com', '', '96.227.23.182', '2009-11-16 22:44:11', '2009-11-17 02:44:11', '\"I must try harder.\" Words to live by.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_6; en-us) AppleWebKit/525.27.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/3.2.1 Safari/525.27.1', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30416', '346', 'MoGa', 'molly.gaudry@gmail.com', '', '96.227.23.182', '2009-11-16 22:46:42', '2009-11-17 02:46:42', 'I was also going to suggest City Lights.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_6; en-us) AppleWebKit/525.27.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/3.2.1 Safari/525.27.1', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30417', '333', 'MoGa', 'molly.gaudry@gmail.com', '', '96.227.23.182', '2009-11-16 22:48:25', '2009-11-17 02:48:25', 'My students really responded well to \"This Program Contains Actual Surgical Procedures.\" Thank you for that. Thank you.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_6; en-us) AppleWebKit/525.27.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/3.2.1 Safari/525.27.1', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30586', '362', 'Tim Jones-Yelvington', 'timjy@sbcglobal.net', 'http://perverseadult.blogspot.com', '173.15.104.171', '2009-12-02 16:57:56', '2009-12-02 20:57:56', 'I agree removing the taboo from rejection is healthy for everyone. I feel like if done correctly (as in not in that freaky editor-bashing cuckoo-bird way some folks do it), writing about rejection should only contribute to folks\' respect for editors by encouraging folks to take shit less personally and see it\'s all part of the process, as you\'ve said in the past. \r\n\r\nI just got the same Kenyon email. I also came home from Europe to paper slips from Shenandoah, Iowa and Harpur Palate, and email rejections from failbetter and... somebody I else I think.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.5) Gecko/20091102 Firefox/3.5.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30429', '346', 'jensen', 'jensen.whelan@gmail.com', 'http://jensenw.blogspot.com', '128.119.178.26', '2009-11-17 18:06:20', '2009-11-17 22:06:20', 'the juniper contest which is run through umass and umass press has a wide aesthetic. the contest is closed for this year, but next year, you should check it out. esp. for the haiti book, maybe?', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.3 Safari/531.9', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
