('30608', '359', 'michael james', 'iamnotspikelee@gmail.com', '', '65.208.14.238', '2009-12-03 10:43:24', '2009-12-03 14:43:24', 'well, it may not be that the stories arent as strong as you thought, but its just that the (ugh) \'market\' isn\'t ready right now. i believe there are a few stories out there of people trying to place books/stories and failing, then waiting for time to pass, not really touching the projects, then resending them out and all of a sudden KERPOW! they\'re picked up...\r\n\r\ni believe the global hum (known as white noise) combined with the vibes of us all sometimes have a bit to do with how/when/if something is picked up. I know, metaphysical mumbo jumbo, butcha never know.\r\n\r\nand massages with oils and candles and a good tv show or music on tends to help with those rejections.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.0.4) Gecko/2008102920 Firefox/3.0.4', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30603', '362', 'david erlewine', 'daveerlewine@yahoo.com', 'http://www.whizbyfiction.blogspot.com/', '206.138.130.2', '2009-12-03 07:42:44', '2009-12-03 11:42:44', 'hmm, roxane, i\'pm probably out of it but i had no idea people thought it was poor form to blog about rejections.  \r\n\r\nwhy should it be secretive?  i\'m just too lazy to blog about such things but definitely enjoy reading about your rejections and acceptances and other thoughts. \r\n\r\nkeep on trucking as jerry once said.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30605', '362', 'Eric Beeny', 'ellipsis81@netzero.net', 'http://ericbeeny.blogspot.com', '74.78.90.7', '2009-12-03 09:45:25', '2009-12-03 13:45:25', 'Hang in there, Roxane. It seems winter isn\'t just a phenomenon of climatic weather, as the sunshine of acceptances is dwindling and the rejection slips are snowing on lots of us. But seasons are only temporary. No worries--you\'re going to be fine...', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('30607', '362', 'Bill', 'billbozzone@yahoo.com', '', '148.166.161.137', '2009-12-03 10:24:12', '2009-12-03 14:24:12', 'I know the feeling. Johnny America accepted a story of mine pending \"some tightening.\" After revision, they rejected it. Usually when a mag asks for rewrites, I move on. In my experience, they almost never accept the rewrite.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.0; Trident/4.0; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; InfoPath.2; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; OfficeLiveConnector.1.3; OfficeLivePatch.0.0; .NET CLR 3.0.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
