('30454', '315', 'Colin Fleming', 'flemingcolin@comcast.net', '', '24.147.177.168', '2009-11-19 19:39:28', '2009-11-19 23:39:28', 'Hi Roxane,\r\nJust discovered this journal, and wanted to get in touch and salute your perseverance. I write for places like Rolling Stone, The Atlantic, and The New Yorker, and contribute fiction to Boulevard and TriQuarterly, and my God--publishing is unlike anything I\'ve ever heard of, read about, seen, etc. If it makes you feel any better, many of the pieces that I\'ve had picked up by major magazines and journals were rejected hundreds of times. Each. Less than fun. You\'d think the AGNI story would work with some of the 273 places that rejected it, or the Nation piece that had previously gone 0 for 108, but, alas, publishing isn\'t like that. Good luck with everything.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.5) Gecko/20091102 Firefox/3.5.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
