('34485', '571', 'Amber', 'Anoellesparks@gmail.com', 'http://Www.ambernoellesparks.com', '216.164.56.183', '2010-04-01 10:35:47', '2010-04-01 14:35:47', 'If it is, then they are idiots.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (iPhone; U; CPU iPhone OS 3_1_3 like Mac OS X; en-us) AppleWebKit/528.18 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Mobile/7E18 Safari/528.16', '', '34484', '0', 'N'),
('34486', '571', 'Amber', 'Anoellesparks@gmail.com', 'http://Www.ambernoellesparks.com', '216.164.56.183', '2010-04-01 10:41:57', '2010-04-01 14:41:57', 'I agree about the post. I think people just wanted to argue one \"side,\" so they were reducing the complexity of your argument. As if you said the only thing you read was Little House on the Prairie or something.\r\n\r\nAlso, I am very disappointed with One Story for a variety of reasons. (And not just because they didn\'t publish my stories or yours.) I have a subscription but I am not renewing it because I\'ve been really bored with nearly all the stories this last year. I feel like it\'s the same story about the same middle aged woman experiencing some sort of mid life crisis, over and over again. I really respect the editors and they used to publish things like George Saunders so I don\'t get what\'s happened, but the only story I really liked this last year was Seth Fried\'s crazy story about the fair. All the others just seemed so...safe. Meh. I\'m buying a subscription to Ninth Letter instead.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (iPhone; U; CPU iPhone OS 3_1_3 like Mac OS X; en-us) AppleWebKit/528.18 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Mobile/7E18 Safari/528.16', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('34487', '571', 'Tanya', 'LaTanya.McQueen@gmail.com', '', '24.34.197.106', '2010-04-01 10:56:26', '2010-04-01 14:56:26', 'Roxanne,\r\n\r\nTwice in my life I\'ve had my hair fall out to some degree as how you described.  The first was when in college I had my hair chemically straightened.  The owner of the salon who usually did it wasn\'t there and one of his assistants had to do it instead.  I don\'t think she knew what she was doing.  It was not an immediate thing, but my hair fell out in patches.  It sucked.  I\'ve since stopped getting relaxers/my hair straightened.\r\nThe second time was when my mother was going through a losing bout of cancer.  Over the course of several months, my hair broke off and thinned until that summer I decided to cut it all off.  That sucked too.\r\nMy mother had Lupus, which can cause severe hair loss.  She had bald spots that she had to hide by parting her hair an assortment of ways.  Watching her do these things made me realize how much her identity was revolved around her hair.\r\nI want you to know that I feel your pain.  Losing one\'s hair is a traumatic experience.  Even now, years later, I still feel awkward when I don\'t wear my hat, so conditioned I was to wearing it when I felt self-conscious of my hair (or lack thereof).\r\n\r\n-Tanya', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.3 Safari/531.9', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('34489', '571', 'Dan', 'dmoreau@gmail.com', 'http://dlmoreau.wordpress.com', '205.127.185.195', '2010-04-01 13:26:37', '2010-04-01 17:26:37', 'Hi Roxane,\r\n\r\nCorrect me if I\'m wrong (and I probably am) but aren\'t \"most\" of the stories published in One Story excerpted works from upcoming story collections backed by big time publishers? In other words, aren\'t most of the writers they publish firmly established or at the very least have a book deal? At least that\'s my take on One Story.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US) AppleWebKit/532.5 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/4.1.249.1045 Safari/532.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
