('34836', '634', 'Savannah Schroll Guz', 'savannahguz@yahoo.com', 'http://www.savannahschrollguz.com', '71.61.41.245', '2010-05-05 08:15:19', '2010-05-05 12:15:19', 'I just stopped by on my way to find a June 2010 online calendar, and I laughed so hard at this I totally forgot what I was doing. Yes, I love the coy look Kobe is offering the camera with that snowy fedora and terrycloth headband combo. And the disembodied hoodie with the twin burros tails dangling at the neckline? Such seriousness. \r\nAwh! Yes I so sympathize with you on the whole academic grad work process. Mine was only a master\'s thesis (in art history), but it was harrowing on many of the same levels. Programs have a tendency to fill grad students to the brim with self doubt (at least mine did...it was a subtle exertion by only a few faculty members, but it was tremendously effective: ucer anyone? Well then how about a drinking problem?). And honestly, I felt slightly less than sane until I was finally done and did my colloquium, which was our equivalent to a defense (but of course, not the same as having to parry and dodge pointed questions from a panel for an hour and a half). Really, though (and I know it may not help to hear it now, but I\'m positive of this fact, having read your other work), you will most definitely kick academic fanny.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/4.0; SLCC2; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30729; Media Center PC 6.0; MDDC; InfoPath.2)', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
