('35144', '688', 'LJ', 'ljose@mtu.edu', '', '67.142.166.29', '2010-06-04 15:13:32', '2010-06-04 19:13:32', 'I wish that some day I\'ll be lucky enough to experience all the responsibilities that come with having a child. And if I am, I shall never tell anyone that their life is \"easier\" because they don\'t have a child. Having a child will be my choice. I\'m just saying. \r\nOne of the most beautiful definition of love: someone who will lie with you on the bathroom floor when you\'re sick.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.2.3) Gecko/20100401 Firefox/3.6.3', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('35145', '688', 'Eric', 'ebennett@tkc.edu', '', '67.85.139.164', '2010-06-04 15:51:05', '2010-06-04 19:51:05', 'Roxane,\r\n\r\nI\'ve been an \"I Have Become Accustomed To Rejection\" voyeur for some time. Today, however, I am compelled to out myself in response to your comments about providing feedback with rejections.\r\n\r\nFuck the people who don\'t want feedback. Let them insert their shiny prose into the slot of some editorial vending machine. But don\'t let them ruin for us the one magazine that takes time to provide candid feedback. Don\'t let them ruin for us the opportunity to work with one of the best goddamned editors out there - you.\r\n\r\nWriters who are serious about their craft want to get better, want feedback from editors who know their ass from an interrobang. Yes, it pisses me off each time you reject my work – but in the end it serves to strengthen the story or my resolve that it\'s a great story as is. Either way, your feedback makes me a better writer.\r\n\r\nI\'m angry that a few candy-asses who can\'t take a little rejection are whining about it. Perhaps they should consider a safer sport, one that won’t bruise their shins or scrape their elbows. \r\n\r\nFuck \'em, Roxane, fuck ‘em.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; InfoPath.2; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.30; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.648; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('35146', '688', 'Eric', 'ebennett@tkc.edu', '', '67.85.139.164', '2010-06-04 15:53:16', '2010-06-04 19:53:16', 'I love So You Think You Can Dance, by the way. And I hate Nicolas Cage.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; InfoPath.2; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.30; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.648; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
