('35383', '739', 'Tres Crow', 'trescrow@gmail.com', 'http://www.dogeatcrow.blogspot.com', '12.159.49.23', '2010-06-21 09:10:49', '2010-06-21 13:10:49', 'I have to agree with Jake. That pretty much sums up my experience of 20+ years of watching the Coast Guard Festival parade in Grand Haven. Last time I was there it dawned on me what a strange, trite little tradition parades are, and whether there was maybe something deeper about the Middle American psyche waiting to be explored there. Then I went and got a funnel cake and forgot about it, until just now.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows NT 5.1; SV1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.30; .NET CLR 3.0.04506.648)', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('35174', '670', 'LA Slugocki', 'laslugocki@gmail.com', 'http://talesfromthevelvetchamber.blogspot.com', '74.73.240.205', '2010-06-06 08:44:28', '2010-06-06 12:44:28', 'I started watching SATC when I was desperately sick with the flu.  Before that, no way.  Not this woman majoring in feminist archetypal theory at NYU. But what can I say, I loved it.  It reminded me of how much fun I had playing with my Barbie dolls. I forgot all about my 102 fever.  It has nothing to do with real life, as you say, and when people told me I reminded them of Samantha b/c I was single and blonde, I was astounded. Carrie\'s apt. and her wardrobe on that salary? Never.  More likely she\'d be living in a walk up in the East Village with two other psychotic roommates. But the shoes! The hair!  The dresses!  After awhile I forgot that my professors all despised the series, I\'ll still watch it on reruns late at night.  Its a shame it became a franchise.  I agree 100% that Salon should pay you BIG $$$$ to review movies.  A suggestion?  Try Huffington Post, they don\'t pay, but worldwide exposure.  p.s. please don\'t think I\'m stalking you.  you have an amazing voice.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
