('37006', '939', 'Terri', 'tfredrick@gmail.com', '', '173.31.46.135', '2010-09-01 22:53:03', '2010-09-02 02:53:03', 'Ok, I was wrong. I am totally commenting on your blog because I have two v. important things to say:\r\n\r\n(1) When something is so good that it\'s practically free, that\'s known as \"cheap as free.\" It\'s a brilliant thing to say and it confuses all who hear it, so...bonus.\r\n\r\n(2) Sometimes beautiful people are not required to be anything other than beautiful. And despite what I will admit is a strangely irregular head shape, Idris Elba is beautiful. It\'s possible that some form of winter blindness from too many years in the UP prevents you from seeing his beauty.\r\n\r\nOh wait, one more...\r\n\r\n(3) I like to talk in numbered points. It\'s the engineer\'s daughter in me probably. And now you know this.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.8) Gecko/20100722 Firefox/3.6.8 ( .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('36236', '882', 'Amber', 'anoellesparks@gmail.com', 'http://www.ambernoellesparks.com', '208.118.163.99', '2010-08-02 14:45:10', '2010-08-02 18:45:10', 'This is exactly like when Barack Obama at that graduation speech where he said something about the kids and their twittering and internets and video gaming and blogginess. It was like, Barack, please. Your entire campaign was run online, practically, and you made numerous reference to your iPod and your Blackberry and various hip-hop stars, but now you\'re all, Oh, I don\'t get technology, I\'m an everyman, see?\r\n\r\nI think people do think it makes them an everyman. I roll my eyes, because the fucking 40 year olds at the grocery stores that my union represents spend all their time on Facebook on their smartphones. It just shows how truly out of touch these celebrities are, that they think the little people can\'t, like, get technology somehow. Like the intertubes are only located in New York and LA or something.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.2) Gecko/20100316 Firefox/3.6.2 GTB7.1 ( .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('36706', '918', 'Dawn.', 'ladyjanetulle@gmail.com', '', '24.131.106.70', '2010-08-18 11:54:10', '2010-08-18 15:54:10', 'I can\'t believe SLQ rejected you because your stories are SO EFFING FIERCE and SLQ just accepted one of mine (I believe for the upcoming quarterly because they requested an interview), which pales in comparison to ANY story I\'ve read of yours, IMO. You, Ethel Rohan, Elizabeth Ellen, Mary Miller, and Claudia Smith are like my Fab 5 right now.\r\n\r\nYes, I am that much of a fangirl about writers. I shamelessly use phrases like \"Fab 5\" and squealed and hopped around when Mary Miller\'s <i>Less Shiny</i> came in the mail.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.8) Gecko/20100722 Firefox/3.6.8', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('36295', '884', 'extie ecks', 'notimetosayit@gmail.com', 'http://www.notimetosayit.com', '74.7.71.73', '2010-08-04 12:41:40', '2010-08-04 16:41:40', 'SPN,\r\nI guess I can understand why that might unsettle you, a writer saying they love a story they wrote because maybe it sounds boastful?  But, as someone who writes stories, I would not share stories I had written with the entire world unless I loved them on some level.  And, if I loved them on some level, why not say so?  Or you could say, Hey, here are two stories I wrote, they are just okay and potentially might suck but then nobody would probably want to read them.  Why can\'t we be publicly proud of our work without it being \'unsettling\'?  I think it\'s different if Roxane had said, here are two of my stories that kick your story\'s ass or here are two stories and my shit never stinks or some other nonsense, but she didn\'t.  Roxane is a lover of the written word and if her words are the ones she loves...which she SHOULD...then why not present them that way?\r\n\r\nNot arguing. Just thinking out loud.\r\n\r\nAlso, Peter North was an 80\'s porn star.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; GTB6.5; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; InfoPath.1)', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
