('36829', '930', 'Roxane', 'rgay74@gmail.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '66.116.8.109', '2010-08-23 17:00:41', '2010-08-23 21:00:41', 'God, there was so much to unpack in the movie. I completely forgot about the blatant inconsistencies. The chopper chase was baffling as was dragging the general\'s daughter around. Did Eric want her for himself? So confusing. I literally LOL\'ed when she didn\'t have a mark on her after like 2 days of serious torture but I think she probably has magic skin. And a magic white shirt.\r\n\r\nI don\'t understand why they didn\'t follow through with the romantic story line between Sly and the girl.\r\n\r\nJet Li WTF?? WHY DID HE NEED MORE MONEY? DID HE HAVE A FAMILY EVEN THOUGH HE SAID HE DID AND THEN SAID HE DIDNT? Why is it so confusing?\r\n\r\nAnd OMG, the weird tattoo soon. They didn\'t even TRY to make it look realistic. So amazing.\r\n\r\nAnd yes, a lot of fun. I really enjoyed myself.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.9.0.19) Gecko/2010031422 Firefox/3.0.19 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '36827', '0', 'N'),
('36827', '930', 'xtx', 'notimetosayit@gmail.com', '', '74.7.71.73', '2010-08-23 15:22:16', '2010-08-23 19:22:16', 'all of the above!  also,\r\n\r\n-I loved how Sly sat down to get his tattoo finished, literally moved around for two minutes and then, poof! it was finished!\r\n\r\n-WTF with running for the chopper for 20 minutes at the end.  How big was that compound?\r\n\r\n-Why did Eric Roberts need to drag the generals\' daughter with him after the general was already killed?  Why didn\'t she just break from him and run away?  Why, after running through forty-hundred explosions was her face and white blouse perfectly white at the end?\r\n\r\n-WTF with Sly just being \'good\' with a hug from the girl he came back to save (sorta)\r\n\r\n-I love how she gets her face punched before she gets tortured but, then after, no marks on her face at all.\r\n\r\n-Jet Li\'s character was, puzzling.\r\n\r\nanyway. it was all fun.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; GTB6.5; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; InfoPath.1)', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
