('36586', '918', 'KWDragon', 'kwdragon@pasty.net', '', '208.65.26.152', '2010-08-12 22:54:30', '2010-08-13 02:54:30', 'When you have kids, you get things done because you don\'t have a choice.\r\n\r\nYou get up ahead of the kids to write; you learn to write between the slammings of the side doors of the minivan; you write when they have gone to bed.  And, sometimes, when life is good, you put off all those things you don\'t really need to do, and you really enjoy your kids.\r\n\r\nThat is what I am doing this week instead of packing, and it has been sweet.  Sweet like using a sticky glob of honey to raise the yeast in your baking instead of a teaspoon of granulated sugar.\r\n\r\nI\'d rather get to Philly half-naked than miss out on this week.  ;-)', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.2.8) Gecko/20100722 Firefox/3.6.8', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
