('37264', '949', 'Dawn.', 'ladyjanetulle@gmail.com', '', '65.60.229.228', '2010-09-12 13:01:37', '2010-09-12 17:01:37', 'I\'ve considered submitting to Caketrain a few times, but every time I imagine the form rejection I would most certainly receive and I chicken out.\r\n\r\nMo\'nique is annoying. I hate the way she talks too. I also find it interesting that when a black person wins an Oscar, it\'s for playing a villian/really fucked up person (other examples: Halle Berry and Denzel Washington). I will say, I appreciate the hairy legs. I don\'t shave my legs and most people don\'t even notice, even though I\'m light-skinned as hell.\r\n\r\n<i>Sometimes, as I think this, I whisper, “awesome,” out loud because I can’t hold it in, my delight at this turn of events.</i>\r\n\r\nLove that. Congratulations on all the awesome.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.9) Gecko/20100824 Firefox/3.6.9', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('36927', '159', 'Stephan', 'doomguy33@yahoo.com', '', '76.66.183.147', '2010-08-29 21:37:45', '2010-08-30 01:37:45', 'Hi there, I find your writing incredible, quite frankly. WIth that out of the way, I checked out your \"Between Things\", as you recommend, though the images for the Venn diagrams were illegibly distorted in their resizing (does anyone else get that?) (I instead found the links to where they reside, and loaded up their original (\"loose\") size to read them), and I was fascinated. Keep up the good work.\r\n\r\nI sincerely can\'t tell if the story therein is completely based on reality, or if it\'s fictitious.\r\n\r\nWould you please quench my curiosity and uncurtain the wizard, Roxane?\r\n\r\nOr should I say, sorceress?', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 6.0; WOW64; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; Media Center PC 5.0; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30618)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
