('36270', '882', 'd', 'editor@lettersjournal.org', 'http://www.lettersjournal.org/blog', '74.140.162.45', '2010-08-03 23:26:30', '2010-08-04 03:26:30', 'My job is teaching (mostly old) people how to use computers.  I meet 12-40 people a week who do not know how to use computers at all.  Talking about not liking computers makes my students comfortable and happy, so I do that sometimes.  I \'get\' technology but choose not to use a lot of it.\r\n\r\nThere is also a feeling that not-a-computer = authentic, but I think authenticity is a false grail.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; en-US; rv:1.9.2.6) Gecko/20100625 Firefox/3.6.6', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
