('36742', '922', 'Dawn.', 'ladyjanetulle@gmail.com', '', '24.131.106.70', '2010-08-19 14:49:53', '2010-08-19 18:49:53', '<i>I was driving on dark, twisty country back roads the other night. I was alone. I had just been somewhere unexpected and was making my way home. There were no other cars. The narrow, barely paved road was flanked on either side by deep and endless rows of corn, standing tall, ready to be harvested. It was a bit frightening and a bit lonely. I started to worry about whether or not I would make my way to some landmark I recognized, something I could hold on to.  For some reason I decided to look out my window. The sky was so full of stars I felt like I was seeing every star God ever thought to create. I told you that part. What I did not tell you is that  looking into those stars, that breathtaking night sky, it made me think of you.</i>\r\n\r\nFucking beautiful.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.8) Gecko/20100722 Firefox/3.6.8', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('37034', '159', 'Stephan', 'doomguy33@yahoo.com', '', '76.69.167.214', '2010-09-03 22:13:12', '2010-09-04 02:13:12', 'Well, thanks for clearning that up then. :P\r\n\r\nPerhaps put more tersely, you mean to say that your stories are \"facetious\"?\r\n\r\nI do applaud your well-executed slightly self-depracating satire, and I truly think you\'re truly intriguing.\r\n\r\nRather than try separating fact from fiction, I\'ll wish that not all of your hopes and dreams have faded (I think you deserve good things). Your articles sometimes make me feel as though I am not alone. (Most people wouldn\'t find hanging \"polygamist\" dolls at all disturbing, for example.) I guess I\'m really trying to say that they (no, not the dolls--your articles) remind me that I shouldn\'t feel so sorry for myself sometimes...\r\n\r\nYou have a nice website--the colors, fonts and motif are all easy on the eyes. Good job Roxane, seriously. \r\n\r\nThanks for sharing.\r\n\r\n(It\'s a shame that some people may not have the gumption to figure out how to read those diagrams--they really make the piece.)', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 6.0; WOW64; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; Media Center PC 5.0; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30618)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('36332', '863', 'Savannah Schroll Guz', 'savannahguz@yahoo.com', 'http://www.savannahschrollguz.com', '71.61.41.245', '2010-08-05 15:13:29', '2010-08-05 19:13:29', 'I totally agree with LJ. This is fantastic. I always dig your observations. And I laughed hysterically over the gas-pumping story, especially your description of the slow jamz...and the detail of his putting his toothpick back into his mouth: perfect. So, I wonder though, was the guy shirtless and in flip-flops a male prostitute who was doing \'laps\' for advertising purposes? Maybe I\'m being obtuse here, and that\'s pretty much obvious, huh?', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/4.0; SLCC2; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30729; Media Center PC 6.0; MDDC; InfoPath.2; .NET4.0C)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('40597', '1042', 'Rose', 'roseh400@yahoo.ca', 'http://rosehunterblog.blogspot.com', '120.19.13.69', '2010-11-05 02:16:31', '2010-11-05 06:16:31', 'I could relate to a lot of that, especially the love letters / stories, and the things I think are good ideas, but really aren\'t. (For example) I let my driver\'s licence lapse for too long and now I have to do the entire test again. I know I\'d fail without lessons to remember all that stupid stuff that everyone forgets (? right?) as soon as they pass the first time, so I\'m never going to do it. I\'ll never have a driver\'s licence again, for the rest of my life. That\'s not really related to your license plates but I thought I\'d share. Hope this comment is not too dumb. I enjoyed your post, as always! Congrats on those acceptances. :)', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_3; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.21.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.4 Safari/531.21.10', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
