('40666', '1047', 'Dawn.', 'dawngrrrl@gmail.com', '', '65.60.229.228', '2010-11-06 23:03:21', '2010-11-07 03:03:21', 'I want to read <i>Dead Baby Stories.</i>\r\n\r\n<i>I looked up endurance in the dictionary–the fact or power of enduring an unpleasant or difficult process or situation without giving way. When one submits they must often also endure. They must give way without giving way; they must yield without yielding. That particular tension fascinates me.</i>\r\n\r\nLovelovelove this.\r\n\r\nI don\'t trust people who smile all the time. I smile all the time in public and only when I have reason to in private. I guess that means I don\'t want people to trust me. Probably true.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.12) Gecko/20101026 Firefox/3.6.12', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
