('40733', '1053', 'Dawn.', 'dawngrrrl@gmail.com', 'http://nouvelliste.tumblr.com', '65.60.229.228', '2010-11-09 22:25:14', '2010-11-10 02:25:14', 'Re: Zombies, I\'m guessing it\'s similar to why we\'re fascinated with vampires. The desire to/fear of being made into something entirely different from ourselves and the fear of/fascination with our own mortality. Also, zombie stories always have a still-human hero or group of heroes, which allows us to cast ourselves into a survivor role. Everybody wants to be a bad-ass once in a while. But this is just me typing whatever comes to mind.\r\n\r\n<i>There is safety in size. I feel safe. I feel immovable and impervious. The more weight I lose, the less safe I feel. It stresses me out.</i>\r\n\r\nMe too, in a way. The more weight I lose, the less safe I feel, but I prefer feeling less safe. I\'m used to feeling like an exposed nerve so it\'s more comfortable. But that\'s just a symptom of my own personal brand o\' crazy.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.12) Gecko/20101026 Firefox/3.6.12', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
