('40545', '1042', 'xtx', 'notimetosayit@gmail.com', '', '74.7.71.73', '2010-11-03 17:15:54', '2010-11-03 21:15:54', '1. Your BFF did not pressure you into nanowrimo.  LIAR!\r\n\r\n2. \"STOP. SEND HORSE AND BUGGY. STOP. BRING GAS LANTERN, PETTICOATS AND OPIUM. STOP. IT’S GOING TO BE A PARTY. STOP. YOU’RE WELCOME. STOP.\" lolfr\r\n\r\n3.  \"I want to talk about it but I don’t know how. I don’t know if you want to listen. I don’t know if you’re bored of the topic. In some ways, I am. In some ways, I will (can) never be.\" i do want to listen and i\'m never bored. i cant speak for your other readers though;\r\n\r\n4.  Strange Gods is a story that has stuck with me since you let me read it.  I am so thankful it found an incredible home.  It is an owie story.  It is a necessary one.\r\n\r\n5.  I refresh my emails account a lot too. Ashamedly so.  No good news hardly ever comes.  One day it might hence all the refreshing.\r\n\r\n6.  I know about how the words feel.  I am mostly mad at myself, the vessel of distribution.  I am like the old fangled machine on the factory floor that produces 20x less than all the new bright and shiny machines.  Management only keeps it around to remind themselves how far they\'ve come and they sort of laugh at it in a good natured way.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; GTB6.5; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; InfoPath.1)', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('40547', '1042', 'Shannon', 'shannons.chiaroscuro@gmail.com', 'http://shannon-writes.net', '66.54.143.6', '2010-11-03 19:53:24', '2010-11-03 23:53:24', 'I\'m doing Nanowrimo too. I\'ve done it before but this is the first year I\'m actually trying to end with something that\'s not just pure self indugence.  I\'ve been getting those kinds of rejections a lot lately too. The one that really bothers me is when you get automatically subscribed to a mailing list. That chaps my ass.\r\n\r\nI\'m happy about your acceptances too I just started reading Brevity recently and I dig it.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.12) Gecko/20101026 Firefox/3.6.12 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('40570', '1042', 'david e', 'daveerlewine@gmail.com', '', '206.138.130.2', '2010-11-04 14:14:11', '2010-11-04 18:14:11', 'Fantastic re BWR.  Wow, that is huge.\r\n\r\nYou can do a marathon.  I trained for about seven weeks and did my first last month, after spending much of my 37 years never thinking I\'d ever want to run one, let alone actually complete one.  I hated running until a few years ago but had never run more than 11 miles before I started the seven-week training.  Great music is key.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('40571', '1042', 'Ethel Rohan', 'ethelrohan@gmail.com', 'http://ethelrohan.com', '76.103.51.140', '2010-11-04 14:42:30', '2010-11-04 18:42:30', 'Roxane, I think I could have wrote this post, except I\'m not doing NaNoWriMo and I didn\'t receive those excellent acceptances. Congratulations. \"Strange Gods\" is a brilliant story.\r\n\r\nMaybe it\'s not so much that we\'re all the same, but that we\'re all dealing with at root the same things and it\'s how we navigate it all that sets us apart. I think a marathon is an excellent goal and I\'ve been toying with the idea myself. I\'m also trapped in Suckville, again!, and need to find a way out. Let\'s run, run!\r\n\r\nCongratulations again.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_4; en-us) AppleWebKit/533.18.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.0.2 Safari/533.18.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('40572', '1042', 'Jason', 'enricopallazo@yahoo.com', 'http://www.jasonmjones.net', '65.242.114.226', '2010-11-04 16:26:05', '2010-11-04 20:26:05', 'The Los Angeles Review note reminds me of Glimmer Train\'s \"Because we read so many stories, it is not possible for us to give specific feedback, but, if you\'re a relative beginner, you may find something of interest here: Editors\' Input.\" The first time I got that I was like wow, they must think what I\'ve sent them is really bad (actually it was), and I was hurt for a moment (I was well aware to avoid overusing adverbs). I\'ve sent them stories since that I think are much better and each time that same line is in the rejection. I think it\'s pretty standard and so I\'ve learned that whenever you see something like this in a form rejection, you can\'t really take it to heart (the one line that gets on my nerves most, however, is the whole \"Because we\'re writers too, we understand...blah, blah, blah\"....yes, please stop patronizing me.)\r\n\r\nAt the same time, I would assume that the Los Angeles Review\'s PS was meant with the best of intentions (getting you to subscribe) and wasn\'t mean to say \"How could you believe we\'d ever publish this!!!?\" But since I don\'t know the editors, that\'s just a sneaking suspicion.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.12) Gecko/20101026 Firefox/3.6.12', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
