('40759', '1053', 'paula', 'pbomrock@yahoo.com', 'http://www.paulabomer.com', '72.225.175.151', '2010-11-10 19:44:59', '2010-11-10 23:44:59', 'I\'ve lost ten pounds and can\'t wait to start lifting and get it back.I miss my guns. \r\n\r\nIove most Vampire movies- Let the RIght One In (I read the book first)but zombies confound me.\r\n\r\nWe are all flesh and blood,but I believe in  the  spirit. \r\n\r\nI  have had the same psychologist for 20 years. I have dedicated my  first book to him and then, added my father.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US) AppleWebKit/534.7 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/7.0.517.44 Safari/534.7', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('40775', '1053', 'ch', 'craighartglass@gmail.com', '', '67.87.5.158', '2010-11-11 14:55:50', '2010-11-11 18:55:50', 'Roxane, no one who has ever read your writing would tell you you can\'t fly.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/533.18.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.0.2 Safari/533.18.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('41225', '1089', 'Dawn.', 'dawngrrrl@gmail.com', 'http://nouvelliste.tumblr.com', '65.60.229.228', '2010-11-28 21:54:11', '2010-11-29 01:54:11', 'Love this post. Especially this:\r\n\r\n<i>As a writer I have found one of the stories I want to write over and over again. It’s an important story, to me and I think to others. I want to get better about writing that story.</i>\r\n\r\nand this:\r\n\r\n<i>I have a real sympathy for the bad men because most of the time they aren’t all bad and if they are bad, they generally had help getting that way. I try to understand their motivations, what makes them think they have the right to do the things they do. I try to explore whether or not they feel guilt or remorse. I try to understand how they became broken. When I write good men, I try to understand how they managed to stay good. I know far more good men than bad men. My writing doesn’t necessarily reflect that but I do write fiction after all.</i>\r\n\r\nand this:\r\n\r\n<i>There isn’t a right way or wrong way to write women, or men, though I certainly believe some ways are more right than others. With each story, what I’m trying to do is this: I am trying to get it right.</i>\r\n\r\nP.S. I linked to <i>Lacrimosa</i> <a href=\"http://nouvelliste.tumblr.com/post/1721441946\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>. :)', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.12) Gecko/20101026 Firefox/3.6.12', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
