('41088', '1089', 'jack', 'jackdiane@yahoo.com', '', '99.157.18.199', '2010-11-25 16:39:17', '2010-11-25 20:39:17', 'So your agent is trying to place stories for you? I\'m asking because I just landed an agent--a pretty big one--for my short story collection, and am wondering if this is even a good idea, since collections are such a tough sell. Don\'t want to waste the agent\'s time or mine. I know this is a public forum, but has your agent had much success placing your stories?', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.0; Trident/4.0; SLCC1; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; Media Center PC 5.0; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30618; .NET4.0C; BO2IE8_v1;ENUS)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('41091', '1089', 'Julie', 'julieinnis@gmail.com', '', '24.45.8.215', '2010-11-25 17:50:06', '2010-11-25 21:50:06', 'Loved the post, but this in particular struck a chord:  \"When I’m writing about women, I’m trying to find ways to convey how hard it is to be a woman without making it seem like it’s something that needs to be pitied or valorized. Because it isn’t. Life is hard for all of us but life is also pretty grand. If it wasn’t hard, I don’t suppose it would be as interesting.\"  Grateful for these words today, thank you for sharing them with us.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 999.1; Unknown)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
