('41859', '1124', 'Babe Runner', 'letitiamoffitt@yahoo.com', '', '98.212.150.247', '2010-12-11 21:00:16', '2010-12-12 01:00:16', 'I agree with you about BASS. Totally predictable selections once again.\r\n\r\nAs a marathon runner, I support your endeavor 9,000%, or whatever the going rate is for hyperbole these days.  However, I will suggest that you enjoy the journey and not focus solely on the destination, so to speak.  I love running, and for me training for marathons is just as satisfying than completing them.  Training reminds me that marathons are difficult, and that they take a lot of time and effort -- which is why they are worthwhile.  Yeah, I know, it sounds sick and twisted to suggest that training is enjoyable, but it is.  The marathon is just the icing on the (heavily carbo-loaded) cake.  Welcome to the sick, twisted world of distance running.  Mwa ha ha...', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
