('41372', '1115', 'Terri', 'tfredrick@gmail.com', '', '139.67.92.67', '2010-12-01 12:08:21', '2010-12-01 16:08:21', 'You should do all your shipping from EZ Parcel in Mattoon. Seriously. The woman who works there is brilliant. Since she can ship USPS, FedEx, or UPS from the same machine, she\'ll always get you the best deal. And you don\'t need to know anything. You can walk in and say, \"I want to send this book to my friend Suzie. I think she lives in Oak Park or something\" and she will figure out where to send that damn package. I don\'t fill out my own address labels. I don\'t pack the shit in the box. I just hand her a stack of stuff and the post-it note with the address and she does a thing and I\'m out the door three minutes later. It\'s beautiful.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.2.12) Gecko/20101026 Firefox/3.6.12', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
