('44538', '1314', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '66.116.8.109', '2011-02-20 21:10:25', '2011-02-21 01:10:25', 'Lord, we really should feel sorry for our SOs. It\'s a lot to ask someone, I sometimes think, to put up with a writer. That\'s why I generally do not date writers. There can be only one!\r\n\r\nI do agree with what you say here about rejection being useful. If a given story receives enough rejections, I go back to the drawing board with it, trying to identify where it\'s going wrong. It can be so hard to know why a story isn\'t working given how few editors give feedback. I get why it is impossible to give writers feedback given the number of submissions so many magazines receive but I often wish for a little guidance.\r\n\r\nI am hugging my Black Swan so tightly. Her feathers are sharp.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_6; en-US) AppleWebKit/534.13 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/9.0.597.84 Safari/534.13', '', '44508', '1', 'N'),
