('46903', '1635', 'Jesse', 'jesse@jessecrockett.com', '', '70.245.161.207', '2011-06-19 16:21:08', '2011-06-19 20:21:08', 'I\'ve gotten in the habit of saying \"hi!\" when people ask how I am, unless they are some authority, then I resort to \"okay,\" but I rely on charity to a significant degree.  I don\'t know, but I tell myself that ugly feelings are a sign of growing inner strength.  Actually, I just made that up.  I hope it\'s fine.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_7) AppleWebKit/534.30 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/12.0.742.100 Safari/534.30', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('46785', '1559', 'paula', 'paulabomer@gmail.com', 'http://www.paulabomer.com', '72.225.175.151', '2011-06-01 18:22:22', '2011-06-01 22:22:22', 'I love that list of books. You could throw in some Tolstoy \"The Kreutzer Sonata\" is not too long.\r\n\r\nI wish I hadn\'t deleted the email/blog things my trainer, Clavel, sends out.  But the last one was about how EVERYONE hates working out, and if they say otherwise, they are liars. You do it for how it makes you feel in the long run...calmer, healthier, stronger. I can get endorphn rushes, but only after passing a certain point, and until that point, I am pure misery. Today, I did a \"navy seal\" training on a TRX (look that up, its awesome torture)  with Clavel, who is a 300 pound body builder. It was shaming. I felt like I might barf at one point. Or pass out. And now, well, I get to drink wine and eat a big burger.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/534.24 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/11.0.696.71 Safari/534.24', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
