('43872', '1246', 'Casey Hannan', 'knittingkneedle@gmail.com', 'http://www.casey-hannan.com/', '69.76.186.26', '2011-01-28 10:57:26', '2011-01-28 14:57:26', 'There are those publications that seem like uncrackable eggs. SmokeLong is one of them. I have a submission to them that\'s currently \"In Progress\". It\'ll take days or more (the agony!) before they let me know. I try to divine something in the time it takes for publications to respond after that update in status, but it seems arbitrary. Again, what delightfully indulgent problems to have. I\'m going to sit back and have a sweet tea and wave at cars as merrily they roll along.\r\n\r\nI need Normally Special like I need clean drinking water. It will help me solve all my problems, I am sure.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20101203 Firefox/3.6.13', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('44625', '1314', 'Daniel Parks', 'danielpatrickparks@gmail.com', '', '64.203.40.51', '2011-02-22 04:32:02', '2011-02-22 08:32:02', 'Just knowing that other writers are going through the same thing is a kind of validation. Thanks, and keep up the good fight. Bukowski said something once about how he almost gave up after so many rejections but he knew if he just kept an ember burning inside that the ember could one day start the greatest fire. Keep yours burning until it sets all those magazines on fire.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20101203 Firefox/3.6.13 ( .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('44907', '1346', 'Barry Basden', 'camrocpress@gmail.com', 'http://www.camrocpress.com', '71.115.116.153', '2011-02-28 20:28:52', '2011-03-01 00:28:52', 'Oscar, we\'ll call him Oscar. We\'re in a bar Friday night (after checking in with the Sacto home office) in Gallup fucking New Mexico and he\'s lamenting how Rose, before they were married, was so hot. Couldn\'t get enough of him. Now it\'s all, what happened? Why did it turn to shit? She\'s absolutely passionless...\r\n\r\nWe\'re drunk enough to check out of our motel for the weekend and head for Mexico (before all the beheading bullshit) but it\'s snowing and all the bridges give the Chevy the shimmy shimmy shakes and we don\'t get 20 miles before we turn around and have to beg the asshole clerk to get our rooms back.... Made it to work Monday on the rez, no sweat. \r\n\r\nThat was 25+ years ago. I looked him up on the internet a while back and he\'s still in Sacto with Rose. There are two grown kids, so I guess he got a little more after all. But I\'m afraid to ask how he\'s doing.\r\n\r\nMars &amp; Venus. What a goddam living cliche...\r\n\r\nP.S. Hope you had a great time at the ceremony.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20101203 AskTbFXTV5/3.9.1.14019 Firefox/3.6.13 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('46201', '1438', 'W. Lotus', 'wlotus2008@gmail.com', 'http://lotuslandfineart.com/velvetrope', '74.72.218.55', '2011-04-02 01:00:11', '2011-04-02 05:00:11', 'What you say about writing makes sense. In fact, it makes so much sense, I can (and instinctively did) apply it to photography. Your opinion resonated with me, and the resonance answered the questions I\'ve been asking myself about what I \"should\" be doing with my photography. Thank you.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; PPC Mac OS X 10.4; en-US; rv:1.9.2.16) Gecko/20110319 Firefox/3.6.16 GTB7.1', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
