('45177', '1365', 'Babe Runner', 'letitiamoffitt@yahoo.com', 'http://baberunner.blogspot.com/', '98.212.150.247', '2011-03-05 10:21:53', '2011-03-05 14:21:53', 'I thought this was very well expressed. People sometimes think they know all there is to know about me because I supposedly put it all out there in my blog. I\'m starting to think if anything these people may end up knowing LESS about me for reading my blog, because they assume they\'ve \"figured me out\" completely based on a few 1000-word posts here and there. They don\'t quite seem to realize how incredibly insulting it is to decide that someone is only as substantive as their writing. It\'s a little like my students deciding that I am my teaching persona exactly -- I\'m \"in love with life\" and \"never have a bad day\" and \"the happiest professor on campus.\" Actual quotes. Oh golly. Where to begin.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
