('44439', '1314', 'Margaret', 'myhyacinthgirl@gmail.com', '', '157.229.245.156', '2011-02-17 10:33:46', '2011-02-17 14:33:46', 'I recently decided to send my work to bigger journals, too. You can tell when I started doing this because my spreadsheet becomes just a big long list of rejections. Your writing is beautiful - I am certain these rejections are just the precursor to lovely acceptances.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; InfoPath.2; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('44442', '1314', 'Jen Gann', 'jngann@gmail.com', 'http://jengann.com', '184.152.65.18', '2011-02-17 11:31:22', '2011-02-17 15:31:22', 'I\'ve been thinking so much about \"that next level\" too, Roxane.  A novel I wrote has garnered interest from agents about half of whom rejected it for being \"too absurd\" or \"unsellable,\" which makes me think \"okay, it\'s not me, it\'s them,\" while the other half have given me the baffling feedback of \"more suited to a short story.\"  I\'m not really sure how to take this, other than to imagine the agents are trying to say, \"Who do you think you are, trying to write a novel?\"\r\n\r\nMy main point is, you\'re the Halle Berry in this situation here, where I am surprised to read that you have the same feelings of doubt and insecurity that I do, because hey, you\'re Roxane Gay, you know?', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.4; en-US; rv:1.9.1.16) Gecko/20101130 Firefox/3.5.16', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('44443', '1314', 'Aubrey', 'aubrey.hirsch@gmail.com', 'http://www.aubreyhirsch.com', '98.245.138.89', '2011-02-17 11:40:59', '2011-02-17 15:40:59', 'I JUST did a post about needing external reinforcements. Check it out: http://www.aubreyhirsch.com/2011/writing-awards-make-me-crazy/ You are not alone.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20101203 Firefox/3.6.13', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('44449', '1314', 'susan', 'susanmmccarty@yahoo.com', '', '24.2.77.39', '2011-02-17 15:30:52', '2011-02-17 19:30:52', 'Love your blog. Right there with you on the rejections and that horrid TV show. What do they want?! (Editors and Shonda Rimes) I don\'t get them. So many rejections this month, so much doubt, so many bad fake doctors on TV.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-us) AppleWebKit/533.18.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.0.2 Safari/533.18.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('44450', '1314', 'Rob', 'robterry@yahoo.com', '', '99.157.18.199', '2011-02-17 16:36:59', '2011-02-17 20:36:59', 'Roxane,\r\n\r\nMy agent is also going out with my collection of stories very soon, which has me quite nervous, since we all know how hard it is to place a collection, which leads me to my question: Has your agent encountered complete resistance when pitching your collection? \r\n\r\nGood luck and I hope to see it published soon.\r\n\r\n-Rob', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.9.0.17) Gecko/2009122116 Firefox/3.0.17 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('44451', '1314', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '64.134.123.253', '2011-02-17 16:42:59', '2011-02-17 20:42:59', 'Hi Rob. No there hasn\'t been complete resistance. My work has garnered interest. I\'m just waiting and waiting for that interest to become something more.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_6; en-US) AppleWebKit/534.13 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/9.0.597.84 Safari/534.13', '', '44450', '1', 'N'),
('42788', '1171', 'Mary', 'maddox.dreambeast@gmail.com', 'http://www.ancientchildren.com', '67.58.226.210', '2010-12-31 14:10:31', '2010-12-31 18:10:31', 'You don\'t think you should have gotten those tattoos? Or did you just say that to placate your mom? I like them. They tempt me to get a tattoo of my own even though I\'m way too old for that shit.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/4.0; SLCC2; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30729; Media Center PC 6.0; MDDC; InfoPath.2; .NET4.0C)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('44463', '1314', 'Tracy Lucas', 'tlucas.freelance@gmail.com', 'http://www.smashcakepress.com', '68.53.110.51', '2011-02-18 03:59:33', '2011-02-18 07:59:33', 'You are a rock star.  And you don\'t even seem to know so.\r\n\r\nI see it as a show of strength to still need validation. Honestly. One of my goals in life is to make it to the end and still be naive and emotionally vulnerable. I\'d rather be the impulsive, idiot poet than the dried-up curmudgeon in the corner, and sometimes those are the only two paths that seem to lead out of the gray area we\'re all in at the start.\r\n\r\nSome will label that immaturity, and that\'s fine, but it\'s an intentional choice. I hope and pray to remain breakable as long as I\'m here. Otherwise, what\'s the point?\r\n\r\nIMHO, hardening yourself doesn\'t solve anything; it just makes you hard.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20101203 Firefox/3.6.13', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('44491', '1314', 'Dawn.', 'dawngrrrl@gmail.com', 'http://nouvelliste.tumblr.com', '50.4.37.220', '2011-02-19 00:36:59', '2011-02-19 04:36:59', '<i>There is a myth that holding your left hand to the left wall of a maze will always get you out. I do not know if that’s true but I would like to believe it is. For me, writing is my left hand on the left wall. Even if I don’t know how long it will take to get through whatever maze I’m trapped in, I know that as long as I write, my left hand will always be on the wall. I will always find my way out.</i>\r\n\r\nThis is fucking stunning. So true.\r\n\r\nI\'m with Jen--you are totally the Halle Berry in this situation. But it\'s natural to be that way. Many of us are whether we\'re the Halle Berry in the situation or not.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20101203 Firefox/3.6.13', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('44494', '1314', 'Dan Powell', 'danpowellfiction@gmail.com', 'http://danpowellfiction.com/', '79.236.242.70', '2011-02-19 03:14:06', '2011-02-19 07:14:06', 'A lot of you post resonates with where I am at the moment. I\'ve had a a number of things published around and about and am starting to target more challenging markets (though not aiming at the level you are) and getting my fair share of rejections along the way. The fact you would do this whether you get outside validation or not shows you are the real deal writing-wise. I\'ve come to this blog after enjoying too many of your pieces to list here and am sure you\'ll start hitting the spots you are aiming at soon. \r\n\r\nAs for all writers being insecure on some level.  I\'m reading Chekhov\'s letters at the moment and have lost count of how many times old Anton has written someone about his doubts about the quality/future success of his stories. Even the greats, especially the greats struggled continually with wanting to be better. You\'re in good company if you are striving to be better and questioning your work.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_6; en-US) AppleWebKit/534.13 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/9.0.597.102 Safari/534.13', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
