('43573', '1228', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '66.116.8.109', '2011-01-20 16:54:15', '2011-01-20 20:54:15', '1.Writing as scrubbing. That is a great way to think of it.\r\n\r\n2. Anxiety is not rational. Let\'s invent something in the next 2 weeks that will make big pillars drop out of the sky immediately when we need them. OMFG. We\'d be so awesome if we could pull that off.\r\n\r\n3. I am mad at apple too. My Apple nemesis just called my phone and I DIDNT PICK UP. TIME OUT.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_6; en-US) AppleWebKit/534.13 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/9.0.597.45 Safari/534.13', '', '43571', '1', 'N'),
('43571', '1228', 'BFF', 'notimetosayit@gmail.com', '', '74.7.71.73', '2011-01-20 16:41:46', '2011-01-20 20:41:46', 'First of all, a great person who takes wonderful photographs on his iPhone4 once told me, \"The writing is the scrubbing....the writing is the scrubbing...\" and I\'ve found that to hold true.  \r\n\r\nSecond of all, how will you be alone at AWP at ANY MOMENT if I end up going?  We will be together pretend working on our iPhones and hiding behind pillars. (BIG pillars) \r\n\r\nthirdly, i am mad at apple for making you cry outside of your closet.  \'rotten to the core\' oh yes!!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; GTB6.5)', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
