('43568', '1218', 'Liz', 'hildrethabed@gmail.com', 'http://theeffectofsmallanimals.blogspot.com', '208.70.18.60', '2011-01-20 15:57:12', '2011-01-20 19:57:12', '\"If you’re my mother and you’re reading this, I use condoms for arts and crafts projects.\" Post pics?! \r\n\r\nAlso, I went to Ball State and you could dig up writers back then, but it took some work. I guess it\'s SO happening there now. That makes me happy--and kind of jealous. I TAKE 69 TO BALL U! That t-shirt was hugely popular back in the day.\r\n\r\nI think the wide majority of infertility cases are caused by PCOS (polycystic ovarian syndrome) which is an extremely common endocrine condition that causes infertility AND obesity. (You probably already know this.)\r\n\r\nIn other words, PCOS causes infertility and fatness. Just like anorexia causes infertility and starvation. \r\n\r\nBoth skinny and fat people can and do have babies. Sometimes this is unfortunate--though not because of how much any given mother weighs.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_5_8; en-US) AppleWebKit/534.10 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/8.0.552.237 Safari/534.10', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
