('44514', '1314', 'Jason', 'enricopallazo@yahoo.com', 'http://www.jasonmjones.net', '98.114.106.240', '2011-02-19 20:26:48', '2011-02-20 00:26:48', 'PPS, I didn\'t comment on your \"no satisfying ending post\" because I had something out with PANK, and I felt odd commenting with an open submission (i.e. am I trying to be ingratiating?), but now that it\'s passed (and rejection is cool; Jones will rise again!), I\'d like to suggest that one of the most satisfying finales I\'ve ever seen on TV is Six Feet Under\'s last episode. If you\'ve never watched the series, I suggest you should.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20101203 Firefox/3.6.13', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('43476', '1218', 'Sean', 'leapsloth14@hotmail.com', 'http://seanlovelace.com', '71.194.242.181', '2011-01-18 21:20:14', '2011-01-19 01:20:14', 'Wow, what a vast, interesting, wide-ranging post. But I\'ll have to be reductive here. We hunters often fire guns many times with no intent to kill. Especially off-season. Some people shoot guns to shoot guns, period. I shit you not. Like some people drink with no intention of getting drunk. They like the light buzz.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20101203 Firefox/3.6.13', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('45026', '1354', 'Dawn.', 'dawngrrrl@gmail.com', 'http://nouvelliste.tumblr.com', '50.4.37.220', '2011-03-03 01:43:00', '2011-03-03 05:43:00', 'I just got a personal rejection from The Emerson Review too. They solicited me and I made the mistake of rushing a story because of my giddiness over being solicited. Go me. They sure can dole out a curiously pleasant rejection.\r\n\r\nI am so buying The Chronology of Water this Friday when I get paid. There are <b>so</b> many heartbreaking books to read and that\'s one of the main reasons I\'m grateful to be alive.\r\n\r\nAnd P.S. I can\'t believe you made Mr. Rogers both sexy and comforting and it was somehow not that creepy at all.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20101203 Firefox/3.6.13', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('42933', '1170', 'Terri', 'tfredrick@gmail.com', '', '139.67.92.14', '2011-01-04 15:04:13', '2011-01-04 19:04:13', '\"Sadly, and this is where most of these “let’s show off what we can do with a computer” movies go wrong, is that there was no movie.\"\r\n\r\nAhh, yes. This is what I call the Avatar Aquarium Phenomenon. Avatar was beautiful in the same way that looking at an aquarium full of brightly colored and rather strange fish is beautiful. Avatar had no plot, structure, or story in the same way that an aquarium full of a random assortment of fish has no plot, structure, or story. If I were to chart the interestingness of looking at Avatar and an aquarium, they would be similar: an immediate spike of interest and awe at the big picture that is then sustained for a short period of time as each beautiful element is looked at individually followed a steadily decreasing level of interest that drops into a hypnotic trance almost indistinguishable from sleeping.\r\n\r\nSo many movies suffer from AAP. I think I\'ll just go look at my fish.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20101203 Firefox/3.6.13', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('43603', '1228', 'Amy', 'newnonfiction@gmail.com', 'http://www.amywhipple.com', '24.131.254.156', '2011-01-20 22:29:51', '2011-01-21 02:29:51', 'I\'m sure you\'re Miss Popular, but if you ever need a lunch buddy, consider yourself with a date. (=', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US) AppleWebKit/534.10 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/8.0.552.237 Safari/534.10', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('43602', '1228', 'Sara H', 'ssink83@gmail.com', 'http://glorifiedloveletters.blogspot.com', '98.127.56.12', '2011-01-20 22:05:28', '2011-01-21 02:05:28', 'I\'ve worked out a way for me to get past the weird social anxiety that does the trick a good percentage of the time. Not always, but it\'ll do. I\'ve been at concerts/readings/etc. by myself several times in the past year and I end up hijacking the one person I know\'s friends. \"Oh hey --- yeah, I did go to school with the singer [or whatever]. And uh, I don\'t know anyone here, so if you all don\'t mind, I\'m just going to pretend I know you, okay?\"\r\n\r\n\"Can I pretend I know you?\" usually gets a laugh. And if it doesn\'t, well fuck them -- I don\'t want to sit with you anyway. *petulant scoff*\r\n\r\nThat said, I\'d totally support at-request pillars. THIS PIECE OF PAPER IS SO INTERESTING. (My phone is cheapo and pay-as-you-go. I can\'t even fake looking at my phone.)\r\n\r\nAnd on the Apple front -- I have a friend who was billed SIX times for an iPhone, yet never received one. Awesome. Because they have that kind of money sitting in a bank account to deduct over and over and over.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US) AppleWebKit/534.10 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/8.0.552.237 Safari/534.10', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
