('45352', '1383', 'Tim', 'timothydicks@gmail.com', 'http://timdicks.wordpress.com', '208.3.139.2', '2011-03-08 18:11:34', '2011-03-08 22:11:34', 'I am consistently impressed/annoyed/bemused by the detail of my students\' absence explanations, both the kind you write about here, where they\'re basically saying, I need to miss the second day in a row because I need to rake my lawn, but moreso the kind where they say, Here is the unusual disease I\'ve come down with and all the symptoms that I am presenting. Really most of the time I\'d just like this: Sorry, I can\'t make it.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.17) Gecko/20110121 Firefox/3.5.17', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('43042', '1176', 'Jason', 'enricopallazo@yahoo.com', 'http://www.jasonmjones.net', '65.242.114.226', '2011-01-07 11:50:20', '2011-01-07 15:50:20', 'I\'ve got a lot of love for AI. He provided some of the most fun experiences I\'ve ever had watching basketball here in the city of brotherly love. I can\'t speak to what demons haunt him off the court, but if he\'d ever decided to show up to practice, he might still be playing in the NBA. Hell, he might even have a few rings. I know it\'s not an exact comparison but when people talk about writing everyday vs. only writing when they\'re inspired, I think about the difference between someone like Michael Jordan and someone like Iverson. You have the talent and show up to practice every day: you win six championships. You have the talent but decided you don\'t need to practice: you head off to the promise land once in a very exciting playoff run only to get stomped out by Shaq and Kobe in 5 games.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20101203 Firefox/3.6.13', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('43043', '1176', 'Babe Runner', 'letitiamoffitt@yahoo.com', 'http://baberunner.blogspot.com/', '98.212.150.247', '2011-01-07 11:56:38', '2011-01-07 15:56:38', '1) I think instead of final exams, I am going to hold a DANCE BATTLE. \r\n2) No one has actually ever read Barthelme. He exists to be name-dropped, not read. Seriously, it\'s in his contract.\r\n3) \"I want to date someone whose family isn’t a major obstacle to our happiness, someone where my family isn’t a major obstacle to our happiness, someone who doesn’t require me to compromise every single thing I want, someone who isn’t sexist or racist or an alcoholic.\" When you find this guy, see if his brother is single too, \'kay? Cuz I\'m apparently as \"picky\" as you are (to the point where people who used to say \"you deserve the best!\" and \"never settle!\" are now looking askance at me and thinking \"maybe you deserve subpar\" and \"settle quickly, please, or you\'ll die single\").\r\n4) I enjoyed reading this. The prospect of reading more of this blog in the future makes 2011 seem not so horrible.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('43045', '1176', 'Sara H', 'ssink83@gmail.com', 'http://glorifiedloveletters.blogspot.com', '98.127.56.12', '2011-01-07 12:20:11', '2011-01-07 16:20:11', 'I haven\'t read Barthelme either. Unless by read you mean \"reading quotes of his that people post while name-dropping him on the internet.\" In which case, yes, I\'ve read him a lot.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US) AppleWebKit/534.10 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/8.0.552.224 Safari/534.10', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
