('44269', '1296', 'Tracy Lucas', 'tlucas.freelance@gmail.com', 'http://www.smashcakepress.com', '68.53.110.51', '2011-02-11 03:01:18', '2011-02-11 07:01:18', 'I hear Oprah say something earlier this week that really stabbed into my core. (I know, I know, everybody overtalks Oprah; but I adore Oprah. Sorry.)\r\n\r\nShe was talking to two twin girls who, since the age of five, had been raped daily by every male member of their family.\r\n\r\nNaturally, the conversation turned to the topic of forgiveness, and The Oprah told those girls that forgiveness is not letting go of what happened, moving on, nor pretending that what happened is, was, or could ever be okay. I\'m paraphrasing that, but this next part is a direct quote, and the zinger: \"Forgiveness is letting go of the hope that the past can be changed.\"\r\n\r\nAnd Sugar. Man, Sugar is on fire. I have never read (or even reread) a single column of hers that I haven\'t wept through.\r\n\r\nIt\'s amazing people we\'re surrounded by. I\'m glad you\'re one of them.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.13) Gecko/20101203 Firefox/3.6.13', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
