('45755', '1417', 'Casey Freeland', 'Howiesgoodies@gmail.com', '', '76.236.25.32', '2011-03-15 01:34:22', '2011-03-15 05:34:22', 'That guy was probably a total dick, but the producers wanted you to react exactly the way you did. They want to get people pissed off at the husband so they\'ll talk about it (like this) and other folks will tune in.  When he said whatever he said about his wife on that show, their collective mouths started watering. That\'s the black hole of reality TV, where no light can live.  If he was supportive and loving and said wonderful things about his wife, I\'m going to guess it wouldn\'t be in your blog. Just a guess. I really have no idea.\r\n\r\nMy wife asked if I wanted to see that film for my birthday on Friday. I\'m thinking no.  :-). Thanks for the review.\r\n\r\nCheers,\r\n\r\nCasey', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (iPad; U; CPU OS 4_3 like Mac OS X; en-us) AppleWebKit/533.17.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Mobile/8F190', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('45598', '1402', 'Rion', 'rion.amilcar.scott@gmail.com', 'http://datsunflambe.blogspot.com', '69.143.239.172', '2011-03-11 23:09:12', '2011-03-12 03:09:12', 'Most media criticism in this country annoys me because it shows no understanding of the practical realities of creating a piece of journalism. And it usually has this smug \"I-can-do-this-better-than-any-journalist\" attitude. Which is bullshit because being a reporter is hard. It mostly misses the nuances. And it is often fiercely ideological, which eschews nuance completely. \r\n\r\nI liked your essay because it was all about nuance. And I don\'t think you conflate the reporter\'s views with that of the people he interviewed. Some commentary did. What it comes down to is the choices the reporter made. He may not even be aware that what he wrote represents an irresponsible POV that only serves to normalize and make excuses for rape. It\'s good that you were able to point that out.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.1.17) Gecko/20110121 Firefox/3.5.17', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
