('47251', '1705', 'KWDragon', 'kwdragon@pasty.net', '', '99.156.221.127', '2011-07-31 09:34:45', '2011-07-31 13:34:45', 'Of course, there is no Woody Allen in the Great White North.  That would require a level of literary understanding that eludes many up here.  Luckily, we have things that blow up on our screens, and Cowboys &amp; Aliens was good.  We enjoyed it.  Waiting for Paris on DVD...\r\n\r\nAlso, you know I went straight to Google Translate.  Bo is taking French again this year; she loves the language.  Her teacher was great.  I am so thrilled about that!  Zo took Spanish, and her teacher was awful.  The teacher taught Mexican slang as \"standard,\" which left me (with some high school training and my Cuban slang) unable to help her with her homework.  She is transferring to German this year and will have the same teacher as Bo.  At least Jim can help with that.  We are optimistic.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; rv:5.0.1) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/5.0.1', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
