('46884', '1616', 'paula', 'paulabomer@gmail.com', 'http://www.paulabomer.com', '72.225.175.151', '2011-06-14 18:12:49', '2011-06-14 22:12:49', 'Barfing. I barfed twice in the past year BEFORE running and I\'ve been running for five years or so, and twice during running I almost barfed, but gagged and burped and snot and spit fell out of my face instead. \r\nAs awful as barfing is, it always makes me laugh. I made my son when he was 7 cry when he barfed on an airplane and I couldn\'t help but laugh. I think my all time favorite scene from a movie is the barf scene in Team America. I could watch that every day and it would be like prozac.\r\nHeat levels and running SUCK. Last summer was 100 degree weather and I can normally run 5-10 with little problem and I couldn\'t make a 3 miler- I had to stop and walk and worry about passing out, my head was pounding and I saw red. Scary. Took at least a half an hour to feel better. More like an hour.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/534.30 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/12.0.742.91 Safari/534.30', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
