('46486', '1498', 'Lam Pham', 'lam.pham.here@gmail.com', 'http://lampham.posterous.com', '76.173.255.48', '2011-04-29 04:42:22', '2011-04-29 08:42:22', 'My boyfriend and I watched William and Kate last week after we\'d discovered that most of the campus scenes were shot at UCLA. \r\n\r\nHorrific. I haven\'t watched something that terrible since Dumb and Dumberer (which at least had a scene with Bob Saget screaming \"shit\").', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_4) AppleWebKit/534.24 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/11.0.696.57 Safari/534.24', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('46792', '1599', 'xTx', 'notimetosayit@gmail.com', 'http://www.notimetosayit.com', '74.7.71.73', '2011-06-03 10:22:48', '2011-06-03 14:22:48', 'Great blog post, Roxane!\r\n\r\nThat food looked amazing! (even though there wasn\'t any meat!) \r\n\r\nI agree with EVERYTHING you said about the hangover.  You forgot to mention how they duplicated the \'musical recap\' in both movies: the first one was Ed Helms at a piano in the hotel room, in part two it was Ed Helms in a rickshaw boat with a guitar.  I mean, it was pretty funny how they essentially made the same movie twice in different clothes.\r\n\r\nRe: Bridesmaids (which was WAY better than H2) I think there is a stigma with women being funny because, on screen, women are expected to be gorgeous and hot and gorgeous and hot women aren\'t (typically) funny or \'allowed\' to be funny...you leave funny to the ugly, fat, weird looking women and men..  I think within the last decade there has been a rise of pretty funny women and people dont know what to make of it but are starting to get used to it.   I think Bridesmaids will be a \'groundbreaker\' in terms of Hollywood now starting to understand that a great group of female comediennes (sp?) CAN carry a film and CAN be hysterical and can be pretty and and and.\r\n\r\nI\'m probably not saying this very well. It\'s early over here.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; GTB6.5)', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('46979', '1662', 'Sara H', 'ssink83@gmail.com', 'http://glorifiedloveletters.blogspot.com', '98.127.57.159', '2011-07-03 17:45:36', '2011-07-03 21:45:36', 'See, Jason Statham can save a bad movie. Jason Statham alone can make bad movies good.\r\n\r\nAs usual, I enjoyed this so much.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.0) AppleWebKit/534.30 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/12.0.742.112 Safari/534.30', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('46349', '1372', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '66.116.8.109', '2011-04-13 22:44:36', '2011-04-14 02:44:36', 'Thanks for the kind words, Tori. I tried to offer a new way of telling this story and I\'m glad it rang true for someone who does academic work on the topic.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_7; en-US) AppleWebKit/534.16 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/10.0.648.204 Safari/534.16', '', '46327', '0', 'N'),
('46640', '1538', 'Babe Runner', 'letitiamoffitt@yahoo.com', 'http://baberunner.blogspot.com/', '50.129.94.145', '2011-05-18 09:25:53', '2011-05-18 13:25:53', 'I think I actually look better with a blurred face. Maybe that\'s a look I should cultivate for always. Your photos are also making me realize that spectating a race may have far more benefits than running one. When you run one, you don\'t get to see all those sexy washboard abs; you\'re stuck staring at the tush of the people in front of you, and if those tushies are nothing special, well, those miles can seem awfully long...\r\n\r\nRegarding people who shout insults from cars at runners (and cyclists, too, my biking friends tell me), this seems to be a common thing, maybe stemming from the relative anonymity and sense of empowerment a car bestows upon stupid, weak people.  As fpr gym behavior, everything you described is why it took me nearly 40 years to get a gym membership (and why I still go at 10 in the morning when I\'m usually the only person there).', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
