('46638', '1538', 'Jesse', 'jesse@jessecrockett.com', 'http://jessecrockett.com', '69.155.41.153', '2011-05-18 03:47:56', '2011-05-18 07:47:56', 'Recently I listened to a long lecture series, intro to Shakespeare.  The professor makes big points about the difference between humanity and the type of behavior of the one who insulted you.  In the lecture, \"Richard [II] only joins the human race in his final moments.\"  Richard might not be half bad, so don\'t be too charitable with actual vicious monsters.  It\'s easy to say, yes, because people insult me, and I know it\'s bad to think of them as subhuman, although I really believe it\'s important to sublimate their behavior as subhuman.  If they can\'t give you at least the benefit of the doubt, they\'re certainly not yet on the list of humans. My 2¢.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_7) AppleWebKit/534.24 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/11.0.696.68 Safari/534.24', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
