('46636', '1538', 'LMF', 'lindsey.freer@gmail.com', '', '173.52.156.103', '2011-05-17 23:13:33', '2011-05-18 03:13:33', 'All the moo\'ing and whatnot which I heard from passing cars (this was particularly true in Queens; in Manhattan one cannot hear anything, too much sound in general) really really hurt at first. It still hurts, when I hear it. But most of the time I have my earbuds in and the sound way up and I just assume that anyone saying something in my direction is saying something nice. Or asking for directions--which actually does happen a lot. No, I do not know where [insert intersection/landmark here] is. (I have a \"Never Give Out Directions When All Parties Are On A Freaking Grid\" rule.)\r\n\r\nIt\'s the strangers at the gym that I couldn\'t handle. I\'d punch somebody, and that would be it.\r\n\r\nYour kiddos are so cute! ;)', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:2.0.1) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0.1', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
