('46541', '1518', 'Jason', 'enricopallazo@yahoo.com', 'http://www.jasonmjones.net', '65.242.114.226', '2011-05-05 11:20:43', '2011-05-05 15:20:43', 'I\'m not sure I\'d consider New England Review the next level for someone who has been published in Mid-American Review and Black Warrior Review. To me, all three tend to fall within the same realm of prestige. Then again, I suppose everyone has their own personal tiers of where they rank journals. Personally I\'ve got four: 1. the top, which would include Atlantic, Harper\'s, New Yorker, Zoetrope, Tin House, and Ploughshares; 2. the really good but smaller ones, which is where New England Review, Mid-American and Black Warrior among a whole host of others like Alaska Quarterly, American Short Fiction, etc. etc.; 3. the pretty good, which at this point, I\'ll refrain from naming, because I don\'t want anyone who edits those journals seeing this and thinking, \"Oh, so he thinks we\'re just pretty good, third tier, does he? Well see who\'s third tier when he submits to us...\" and 4. places I\'d pretty much never send my work because the quality isn\'t very good. Still, I wouldn\'t sweat the rejection from New England Review. From what I\'ve read of your work, you\'re punching their weight; you just haven\'t found the right fit for them.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.3) Gecko/20100401 Firefox/3.6.3', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('46826', '1616', 'katie', 'ktseling@gmail.com', 'http://katie-is-nt.tumblr.com', '76.104.198.23', '2011-06-06 02:14:46', '2011-06-06 06:14:46', 'i puked at a stop on the atlanta train dealy (in seattle, we have no such thing as rapid transit. we have the monorail which is, like, 2 miles long, and the south lake union trolley. yes, the acronym is SLUT.). we\'d just gone to the zoo to see the baby panda because baby pandas are FUCKING CUTE. but i started feeling weird so we caught the train back to our motel. \r\n\r\nall of a sudden, i thought i was dying and i kept swallowing that horrible, squiggly pre-vomit saliva and trying to breathe slowly through my nose until i grabbed my husband and dragged him off at some stop and was going to puke over the railing until i saw there was a lower platform with innocent people and everything was spinning and blurry and panicky and--i think--green, and i finally vomited the hugest vomit i\'ve ever expelled from my gut,  splattered onto the cement in what i\'ve convinced myself was a hidden-from-sight-and-smell place. really, i have no recollection of where it was. i also assured myself that drunk people and small children puke out there all the time and workers have to clean it up and it\'s their job so it\'s ok and my vomit would not bother anybody for long...', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_4_11; en) AppleWebKit/531.21.8 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.4 Safari/531.21.10', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('46543', '1518', 'paula', 'paulabomer@gmail.com', 'http://www.paulabomer.com', '72.225.175.151', '2011-05-05 18:08:13', '2011-05-05 22:08:13', 'I\'m mostly in agreement with Jason. \r\nAlso, keep in mind, not one of Mary Gaitskill\'s stories from her first story collection, Bad Behavior, was published in any journal. Then the book came out- and voila. You have a book coming out. We\'ll send it out to all the contacts we have and all the ones you have in galley form and you\'ll get reviewed. And then- voila. This is my prediction.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/534.24 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/11.0.696.60 Safari/534.24', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('46545', '1518', 'paula', 'paulabomer@gmail.com', 'http://www.paulabomer.com', '72.225.175.151', '2011-05-05 18:20:37', '2011-05-05 22:20:37', 'Also, I watched two LMN last night. Committed and ---one with Yasmin Bleeth(sp) who has a terrible facial scar, goes to jail,gets a new face, and revenged the dude who sent her to jail. It was a beautiful night.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/534.24 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/11.0.696.60 Safari/534.24', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('46548', '1474', 'Boris', 'Borisqtd@gmail.com', '', '98.66.7.126', '2011-05-05 22:44:57', '2011-05-06 02:44:57', 'I can\'t join those little clumps of people either. But I\'ve learned to like this about myself.\r\n\r\nThere\'s a T-Shirt you can buy. It says \"JUST SHY. NOT ANTISOCIAL (you can talk to me).\" I\'m thinking of buying that shirt to improve my clumpiness when necessary.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.0; en-US; rv:1.9.2.17) Gecko/20110420 Firefox/3.6.17 ( .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET4.0C)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
