('46831', '1616', 'Dawn.', 'dawngrrrl@gmail.com', 'http://nouvelliste.tumblr.com', '69.47.141.138', '2011-06-06 22:07:06', '2011-06-07 02:07:06', 'Congrats on the acceptance! Your Sweet Valley essay in Bookslut is fucking amazing, by the way. Especially the last two paragraphs. I was holding my heart and smiling and I didn\'t even realize it until I finished reading.\r\n\r\n<i>Either those people really are as horrible as they seem, and in that, quite comfortable with displaying all manner of mental illness, sociopathic tendencies and such or they’re pretending to be that horrible. Maybe we’re all that horrible only we don’t have an audience.</i>\r\n\r\nI think we\'re all that horrible at times. Our lives just aren\'t packaged for TV and consumed by viewers.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.17) Gecko/20110420 Firefox/3.6.17', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('46676', '1538', 'Louise', 'louiseverona@gmail.com', '', '99.157.208.76', '2011-05-22 01:34:55', '2011-05-22 05:34:55', 'I like your writing and your very, very sweet and honest blog. Please, please lose the gym for exercise. Gyms are almost always a very grim place. Find a trail or park and walk long distances or whatever you feel comfy doing. It is relief and inspiration to be out in nature, away from cars, exercising and walking.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:2.0.1) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0.1', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('47368', '1763', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '66.116.26.170', '2011-08-17 22:45:27', '2011-08-18 02:45:27', 'I really would like to check out a bathhouse. It seems so interesting! Re: The Help, I definitely think power dynamics are at play. It\'s just not the same if a black writer writes white characters. I didn\'t go there in the essay because I wanted to be... as measured as I could (well for me anyway). I am working really hard on men writing women. I used to have no tolerance for it but I\'ve read some things in the past couple years that are just so so good. It depends on the writer and I think the same holds for race. Unfortunately, the bad writers seem to be winning this race. Ha ha. No pun intended. And yes, I suspect you do feel where I am at.\r\n\r\n(There\'s no such thing is frivolous here!)', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/535.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/13.0.782.112 Safari/535.1', '', '47367', '0', 'N'),
