('46855', '1624', 'Elaine', 'elncastillo@yahoo.com', 'http://elainecastillo.tumblr.com', '82.16.99.248', '2011-06-10 05:55:53', '2011-06-10 09:55:53', 'SWEET VALLEY HIGH, AAH.  Your essay is genius and so moving.  (American at school, Haitian at home...)  \r\n\r\nDid you ever read the arc that happens after their prom night, when Elizabeth is drunk-driving Jessica\'s boyfriend Sam home, and they get into an accident, and he\'s killed?  And Elizabeth goes on trial for manslaughter, and during this insane period, Jessica and Todd actually get together.  And they pour all their grief and loss and misery and loneliness and sense of betrayal about Elizabeth into each other, into this fucked up desperate relationship.  It\'s so intense.  You could write a great fanfiction about what happens during those couple of books.  \r\n\r\nTeam Jessica, for real.  (I also liked Lila.) \r\n\r\nCongrats on the Million Writers nom!', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/534.30 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/12.0.742.91 Safari/534.30', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('46786', '1538', 'paula', 'paulabomer@gmail.com', 'http://www.paulabomer.com', '72.225.175.151', '2011-06-01 18:50:52', '2011-06-01 22:50:52', 'I submitted and didn\'t make any list either. Oh well. I am curious to  read the winner, It was written by two people. Hm. \r\nIt took turning forty and contemplating health problems to up my fitness level, so you\'re ahead of many many people. I guess- and I know you\'ll disagree- but if people say nice encouraging things, they aren\'t necessarily being condescending, they may just be being nice. Today, someone said nice job to me- my face was purple, I have this terrible fear of the outline of my vagina showing during various positions of workout, and even when I wear baggie shorts (one trainer called my shorts \"clown pants\", and she had a point)- and I said, \"thank you\". Believe it or not, one can be inspired by all types of bodies and workouts going around at the gym. I know I am.  Of course, I never say anything to others for the most part. But still. \r\nI used to have a fear of the treadmill. Like,I had to take an ativan to run on it. Time helped with that. Still, Three or four time grand slam champ Kim Clijsters fell of one recently and chipped her teeth and thanked the dentist who fixed them when she hoisted her last trophy! HAHA! Let that make you feel better about fear of treadmills.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/534.24 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/11.0.696.71 Safari/534.24', '', '46773', '0', 'N'),
