('46827', '1616', 'Babe Runner', 'letitiamoffitt@yahoo.com', 'http://baberunner.blogspot.com/', '50.129.96.51', '2011-06-06 10:49:25', '2011-06-06 14:49:25', 'Yeah, I know I should probably STFU because I myself hate when really good runners are all kind and encouraging to me after I\'ve done something lame, but too bad, ha ha. \r\n\r\nR, I\'ve puked, I\'ve passed out, I\'ve had to stop running after half a mile because of G.I. distress, I\'ve tripped on cracks in the sidewalk and fallen on my face and broken teeth...you name it, if it\'s embarrassing and painful, it\'s happened to me running, and most of it happened the FIRST YEAR I started running. After that my body kind of sighed resignedly and said, OK, I guess she really means this, and after that we got along much better. And heat? The enemy. In general I would rather be hot than cold, but it really does screw you over when you run. I didn\'t last 4 miles the other day running in this weather, and I\'m someone who did 26.2 on a stress fracture. Don\'t kick yourself. It\'s all part of the weird, sick, masochistic world of running, or something.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
