('47065', '1673', 'Don', 'don@heysmallpress.org', 'http://www.heysmallpress.org/', '74.140.162.45', '2011-07-09 21:07:33', '2011-07-10 01:07:33', 'Damn, the Toya show sounds really depressing.  I have a lot of memories of watching 106 and Park and Rap City on BET growing up.  Then my parents got rid of MTV and BET because they were appalled by how women were represented in music videos.\r\n\r\nI\'ve always dreamed of doing a history of black sitcoms in America.  Cosby Show, Sister Sister, Fresh Prince, Bernie Mac, Family Matters, etc.  There was a wider range of black cultural expression within popular culture before the hegemony of hip hop.\r\n\r\nFor a more current (and less crazy) Bill Cosbyish thing that is more focused on the University experience, check out Thomas Chatterton Williams\' LOSING MY COOL.  It\'s an amazing book, and it\'s discounted on amazon right now: http://www.amazon.com/Losing-My-Cool-Fathers-Hip-hop/dp/B0043RT8TU/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1310257667&amp;sr=8-1\r\n\r\n(Apologies if I\'ve recommended this book to you in the past - I try to spread the word about it far and wide.  It was probably my non-fiction favorite book of last year but seemed really overlooked.  There\'s an excerpt online at n+1 where he talks about being the only black student in the philosophy department and what it was like to study Hegel\'s master/slave dialectic as a descendant of slaves.)', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:5.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/5.0', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('46972', '1662', 'marcus speh', 'marcusspeh@googlemail.com', 'http://marcusspeh.com', '84.190.23.150', '2011-07-02 12:19:37', '2011-07-02 16:19:37', 'roxane, well done. i just saw this movie, too, and it\'s all true. it\'s jason statham, btw, don\'t ask me why i know this. i love the image of sally fields flying around: i must have been on the loo when they edited this into the movie. is she one of the nuns in wing suits who get shot down first because the catholic church helped the decepticons? i also don\'t know how i know this. i am still under shock. the saddest thing is: even if i had read your review, i would have gone seen this movie. \"i am weak\", too. thanks.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_7) AppleWebKit/534.30 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/12.0.742.112 Safari/534.30', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('47192', '1698', 'Jason', 'enricopallazo@yahoo.com', 'http://www.jasonmjones.net', '98.114.79.12', '2011-07-23 17:28:54', '2011-07-23 21:28:54', 'I\'m with you right now on the writing uphill feeling. By nature, I\'m not a naturally patient person, and when I sit at the computer, I just want to start typing. Lately, it\'s not happening as well as I\'d like. I finished a short story two weeks ago that I\'m happy with (waiting to see what my writing group says about it; then I plan to send it to Conjunctions for that Kin issue they\'re doing), but it took about 2 months to write and I have 2 that are close to finished, but I thought I\'d finish them this week, and I just ended up writing 1 or 2 lines. One thing I\'ve learned, however, is not to push too much. Sit down, do it, write that dribble or trickle of 20 words or 30 words, a few sentences. If it\'s not coming to you, just keep yourself in it by opening the document. You might write a few sentences and then delete them the next day, but eventually, your mojo will return. You probably know this already, just reaffirming it...', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:5.0.1) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/5.0.1', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
