('47034', '1662', 'Martin', 'martin.macaulay@gmail.com', '', '92.235.183.52', '2011-07-06 08:48:30', '2011-07-06 12:48:30', '\'Shiteous.\' Brilliant. Over here we use \'shite\' as interchangeable with \'shit\'. Generally speaking \'shite\' is less flexible lexically and really does mean excrement. A comedian recently pointed out that you might say \'this is good shit\' but never \'this is good shite\'. So when I read your word, it\'s either \'shit-eous\' or \'shite-ous\'. Both work, though the latter sounds as though it\'s spoken by someone from Bill and Ted.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (iPhone; U; CPU iPhone OS 4_3_3 like Mac OS X; en-us) AppleWebKit/533.17.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Mobile/8J2', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
