('47456', '1773', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '66.116.26.170', '2011-08-24 02:15:59', '2011-08-24 06:15:59', 'Serah I definitely hear you. What makes discussions about race really hard is that, speaking for myself, when you feel in your bones that something is racist, it is really hard to fathom that someone doesn\'t see that. It\'s just too too close. That said, disagreeing on such matters in no way makes someone racist. The bar for racism HAS to be higher than disagreeing, for example, with an essay. The inadequate forum of commenting makes it really hard to find common ground where it is so very much needed. But yes, it frustrates me that there seems to be so little room for disagreement. I will say that one of the reasons I like sending my work to The Rumpus is that they work really hard to create an atmosphere where civil disagreement is possible.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/535.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/13.0.782.112 Safari/535.1', '', '47455', '1', 'N'),
