('47455', '1773', 'Serah Carter', 'Stickstockstone@gmail.com', 'http://Attheendoftheinternet.wordpress.com', '174.255.40.113', '2011-08-24 02:11:09', '2011-08-24 06:11:09', 'My issue [and I hesitate to call it even that] with your essay on The Help was almost this exact thing- people can\'t disagree anymore. That makes me naive and racist, or you black and angry. For the record, that is without a doubt one of the stupidest things I have ever heard someone say on the internet- and I\'ve been here all my life.\r\n\r\nEven if you don\'t agree with someone, there\'s no need to assume it\'s for a reason so simplistic as \"oh, they must be angry because they\'re black.\" Well, yes, I\'m predominantly Irish, if I say something that gets you pissed does that mean I\'m a stupid drunk? \r\n\r\nI don\'t know, it just baffles me. Bottom line? Trolls will be trolls, no matter how many times they\'ve been published. Black, white, or candy striped, there\'s always a way to be a decent person, even if you really want to tell the other party to go play in a blender. If they can\'t understand that, then they don\'t understand a lot of being human.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Linux; U; Android 2.1-update1; en-us; SCH-I400 Build/ECLAIR) AppleWebKit/530.17 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Mobile Safari/530.17', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
