('47367', '1763', 'Terri', 'tfredrick@gmail.com', '', '139.67.133.26', '2011-08-17 16:53:21', '2011-08-17 20:53:21', 'I was all set to write two things in response to this post, and then I read the last paragraph, which stopped me up short and made those two things seem frivolous.....So then I just sat here for five minutes typing and untyping words trying to think how to respond, but there\'s really nothing I can say except that I hear you. And maybe...if what I think to be true is in fact true...I feel some of where you are.\r\n\r\nAnd now I will say those two frivolous things anyway:\r\n\r\nI love a bath house. It was one of my favorite things of going to Russia. If there were a bathhouse nearby, I would go with you in a heartbeat. I fear I would be disappointed, though, if the bathhouse were all Americanized and people were skulking about wrapped in towels. The purpose of a bathhouse is to OWN one\'s body...its size, its age, its hairiness, etc.\r\n\r\nIn your review of The Help, you compared Stockett writing across race lines to you writing across race lines. I feel there\'s something that I can\'t quite put my finger on that\'s different in those two situations. Something about power? I don\'t think appropriation works equally in both directions. (Then again, I\'m struggling to think of prominent black authors who try to use an authentic white perspective for their work, so I might not have a good counter example to see if my idea really holds up.) I know I\'m rarely comfortable with men writing a woman\'s perspective and can count on two fingers the men I think have done it well, but I don\'t have those reactions when a woman writes male characters. Regardless, Stockett\'s book angers me the way white people who are all into living American Indian culture anger me. I just want to slap their hands and say, \"That\'s not yours! Don\'t you have enough?! Besides, you\'re not even doing it right.\"', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/534.50 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.1 Safari/534.50', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('47376', '1763', 'Dawn.', 'dawngrrrl@gmail.com', 'http://nouvelliste.tumblr.com', '75.180.24.47', '2011-08-18 12:12:06', '2011-08-18 16:12:06', 'Solicitation rejections are a serious burn. I\'ve only had one so far, and it was definitely more difficult to handle than a regular rejection (regular rejections usually don\'t bother me). I felt like they were giving me the virtual version of a parent\'s disappointment face. You know that face. It sucks.\r\n\r\nBig congrats re: NOON and the long short story phase. I\'m in that phase now too. Both writing longer stories and writing slower, rewriting more.\r\n\r\nThankyouthankyouthankyou for writing that essay re: The Help. All that needed to be said and you said it so well. I am beyond sick and tired of white privilege porn, in all its forms, The Help included.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.20) Gecko/20110803 Firefox/3.6.20', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('47377', '1763', 'Dawn.', 'dawngrrrl@gmail.com', 'http://nouvelliste.tumblr.com', '75.180.24.47', '2011-08-18 12:13:33', '2011-08-18 16:13:33', 'P.S. Holy shit that Hobart sale is awesome. I am so getting Issues 11 and 12.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.20) Gecko/20110803 Firefox/3.6.20', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('47392', '1763', 'Dera', 'dwilliamsfrequent@gmail.com', '', '209.129.165.18', '2011-08-19 13:45:40', '2011-08-19 17:45:40', 'I love how you share and bare your soul and you do it so eloquently. When you cuss, it even sounds eloquent and classy. LOL. Getting rejected and not knowing what \"they\" want can be sooo frustrating. I recently was rejected for a writing grant. It didn\'t even get past level 1. The grantor wrote, \"Writing is subjective of course but I have known my board for many years what they will approve and I don\'t want to put you through the process.\" Or something like that. I was immediately stung. Was it that bad? And then I realized, no, it was not. Then I got an invite from the African American Literature class at the college where I work and I read part of my first chapter to my almost completed book and they loved it. The professor, who is also the chair of Afram told me to hurry and get finished so she can make it required reading. My book is damn good! :-)', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 5.1; Trident/4.0; .NET CLR 1.1.4322; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.0.4506.2152; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET4.0C; InfoPath.2)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('47397', '1763', 'Amber', 'anoellesparks@gmail.com', '', '66.44.51.128', '2011-08-19 16:28:30', '2011-08-19 20:28:30', 'White privilege porn, that is just perfect. My whole family was so horribly, dreadfully into that movie because they are all a bunch of lovely people but liberal white yuppies who want to feel really good about themselves. I wanted to pull out my hair and burn it and send the smoke through the phone wires somehow. It makes me so especially angry living here in DC, and seeing wealthy white women\'s kids cared for every day by not only black women, but pretty much every minority and tons of them living as practically indentured servants while these white people congratulate themselves for \"helping out an immigrant.\" Ugh ugh ugh.\r\n\r\nAnd yes, Roxane\'s essay was fabulous. As always. If only my rants were as elegant as hers.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:5.0.1) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/5.0.1', '', '47376', '0', 'Y'),
('47398', '1763', 'Amber', 'anoellesparks@gmail.com', '', '66.44.51.128', '2011-08-19 16:31:28', '2011-08-19 20:31:28', 'Roxane, you are amazing. You are not dead inside--how could you be? Everything that comes out of you is like sparkly gold spikes, like galaxies of weird water--your imagination is vastly more expansive than just about anyone else I\'ve ever known. \r\n\r\nThat said--NOON!!!!!! NOON!!!!!! I am anti-exclamation mark but I will happily overindulge now because holy shit NOON!!!!!! I am so so excited for you. Noon is the shit. You are the shit. \r\n\r\nThat is all.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:5.0.1) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/5.0.1', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
