('47633', '1792', 'Serah Carter', 'stickstockstone@gmail.com', 'http://attheendoftheinternet.wordpress.com/', '68.49.23.28', '2011-09-05 07:06:30', '2011-09-05 11:06:30', 'I\'d heard Shark Night was awful, but I prefer your review to others that I\'ve read. It was more fun. I read the BlazeVox saga and though I haven\'t gone through the motions of actually submitting a manuscript to a publisher, you don\'t need to have the experience to know that that sucks, hardcore. It sucks even more when you\'re talking about poetry, which is a hard sell anyway.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:6.0.1) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/6.0.1', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('47424', '1770', 'j', 'paintinginthegrass@yahoo.com', '', '71.100.19.86', '2011-08-21 13:38:42', '2011-08-21 17:38:42', 'Hey Roxane!\r\n\r\n Have you seen the movie Another Year yet? Aside from it being quite wonderful, I think it is a startling contrast to the issue you repeatedly point out (and I am forever annoyed by). Maybe its a British thing, because I\'ve noticed it before, but the actors are very good actors with very normal looks. They are average, maybe even less than. Yet, the couple is extremely loving and relatively happy and the basketcase friend, who in any other movie would be played by a knock-out, is only real world attractive, not movie-land hot. I was so pleased with this happy couple that I was almost distracted by their ordinary looks (I\'m embarased to say). The man is played by Jim Broadbent, always wonderful, and if he alone had been average, one wouldn\'t notice. (I\'m quite sure you\'ve mentioned the large or dorky man with hot woman paradox before). But, because his wife is so plain (and Age Appropriate!) and yet he still loves her, it becomes almost daring. How sad that it should be daring to cast these talented actors??\r\n\r\nsorry for the long comment, but you always seem to hit on movie issues that bug me too!\r\n\r\n(also loved your article on the sweet valley high books)', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/4.0; SLCC2; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30729; Media Center PC 6.0; HPNTDF; BRI/1)', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
