('47663', '1792', 'Jason', 'enricopallazo@yahoo.com', 'http://www.jasonmjones.net', '98.114.82.10', '2011-09-06 22:20:09', '2011-09-07 02:20:09', 'Here\'s a good vegetarian recipe that\'s pretty easy if you have a food process: \r\n\r\n8 oz. arugula\r\n2. Basil leaves\r\n2 garlic cloves\r\nan avocado\r\n\r\nblend that up and you have  a pesto. \r\n\r\nThen boil some pasta, save a ladle full of salty water, and drain, mix the pesto in, drip in the ladle full of salty water and you have avocado arugula pesto pasta. \r\n\r\nBeautifully alliterative and tasty. I only mention this because I too went vegetarian last August, and quick easy recipes are hard to come by. Of course, this one depends on how accessible/inexpensive avocado is in your area and whether you have a food processor/blender.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:6.0.2) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/6.0.2', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
