('47450', '1745', 'Kevina', 'krcassel@mtu.edu', '', '141.219.208.36', '2011-08-23 13:46:07', '2011-08-23 17:46:07', 'As former president of the Planet of the Apes Club in Dover, N.H. (1974-76ish), I don\'t share your dismay with this flawed flick. Yes, it requires great suspensions of disbelief (those \"regular apes\" who didn\'t get the treatments are pretty friggin smart!) and some grappling with disappointment at Franco\'s milquetoast character. And yes, I picked up on the possible racial undertones as well. But for the most part it was an improvement over the stale 2001 remake of the original and the visuals arrested me and the macho-high--well, that tone was set by the female ape, Caesar\'s mother, so I kind of let it slide. I don\'t disagree with your review. I just must remain true to the spirit of the office I once held.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 5.1) AppleWebKit/535.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/13.0.782.112 Safari/535.1', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('47451', '1745', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', '', '66.116.26.170', '2011-08-23 13:48:39', '2011-08-23 17:48:39', 'Kevina! haha I don\'t think the movie had racial undertones, I was just talking about that opening sequence in fake Africa. I have never seen the original Planet of the Apes. I know nothing about the movies so there is no nostalgia for me. The 2001 remake was so terrible. I did see that. I respect your position, Mr. President.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/535.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/13.0.782.112 Safari/535.1', '', '47450', '0', 'N'),
('47458', '1773', 'Shannon', 'shannons.chiaroscuro@gmail.com', 'http://shannon-writes.net', '174.24.130.124', '2011-08-24 03:40:08', '2011-08-24 07:40:08', 'Roxane everything you said about essays is so relevant to me right this instant. \r\n\r\nEverything about the Help I cannot deal with. I get so angry, deep family blood angry because a lot of women in my family have been the help, I\'ve been the help and it\'s just too much for me. I know rationally I do have things to contribute to the discussions but my heart isn\'t in it enough to get stomped on by people. \r\n\r\nUnfortunately since it is the internet and this is one of those tender places in me (which are more numerous than I\'d thought) I have deiced against reading a lot of commentary or comments about the Help. I\'ve discovered lately I just don\'t have the stomach for some discussions with people.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 5.1; rv:6.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/6.0', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
('47463', '1773', 'Fred', 'Freed@gmail.com', '', '98.212.203.140', '2011-08-24 09:00:46', '2011-08-24 13:00:46', 'Thank you for your passionate honesty. \r\n\r\nHave you seen the web series Awkward Black Girl? You may well love it. Just those three words + .com. First episode (each is about three mins) is on the bottom.\r\n\r\nOff to read your piece on the execrable Help...', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (iPod; U; CPU iPhone OS 4_2_1 like Mac OS X; en-us) AppleWebKit/533.17.9 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.0.2 Mobile/8C148 Safari/6533.18.5', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
