('47769', '1804', 'xTx', 'notimetosayit@gmail.com', 'http://www.notimetosayit.com', '99.89.49.45', '2011-09-10 11:40:23', '2011-09-10 15:40:23', 'i LOVED seeing the movie through your eyes!  So interesting. I loved this movie. I love movies where shit outbreaks and people start dropping like flies except for the \'lucky ones\' who instead have to live with all the apocolyptic outcomes from all of it. Probably why i love stephen king\'s The Stand so very much much MUCH! OMG I LOVE THAT BOOK!\r\n\r\nYou forgot  to mention the best parts of the movie like when the doctor dude tells jude law that blogging is like \'graffitti with punctuation\' and the flash to the monkey cage with VACCINE 33 written on it or when it was DAY 133 cuz those were some great scenes. and Demetri Martin as \'science guy\' made me lol.  I kept waiting for him to draw on the dry erase board using both hands at the same time or whipping out a guitar and singing about cells and infections and shit.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/4.0; SLCC2; .NET CLR 2.0.50727; .NET CLR 3.5.30729; .NET CLR 3.0.30729; Media Center PC 6.0; HPNTDF; .NET4.0C; BRI/1; BRI/2)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('47777', '1804', 'Babe Runner', 'letitiamoffitt@yahoo.com', 'http://baberunner.blogspot.com/', '50.129.97.255', '2011-09-10 14:17:14', '2011-09-10 18:17:14', 'Born To Run is AWESOME.  It is THE BIBLE for crazy running people like me -- and YOU!  Glad you liked it.\r\n\r\nWe have to talk about the Coetzee.  I read it a couple of years ago and I still find myself thinking about it from time to time.\r\n\r\nContagion -- hell yeah.  Let\'s go.  I\'m there.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 7.0; Windows NT 5.1)', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('47806', '1804', 'ann ryles', 'annrylesca@gmail.com', '', '70.137.153.116', '2011-09-11 13:35:26', '2011-09-11 17:35:26', 'Disgrace is one of my favorite novels, for all the reasons you\'ve mentioned.  And Coetzee is one of my favorite writers.  (His literary criticism is as edible as his fiction.)  Late or not, I\'m glad you made it to the party.\r\n\r\nNadine Gordimer had this to say about Disgrace:  \"In the novel Disgrace there is not one black person who is a real human being.\"  What do you think, Roxane?', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/534.50 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.1 Safari/534.50', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
