('47812', '1804', 'Roxane', 'roxane@roxanegay.com', 'http://www.roxanegay.com', '66.116.26.170', '2011-09-11 16:49:44', '2011-09-11 20:49:44', 'Ann, that\'s a really interesting statement from Gordimer. I understand where she\'s coming from but I would tend to disagree. At times, people tend to push political correction to the point where we can\'t portray the Other as anything other than noble because we\'re so afraid of dealing in stereotypes but there are criminals in every walk of life and Disgrace works because everyone is complex and not just white or black or good or bad.  What do you think?', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_8) AppleWebKit/535.1 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/13.0.782.220 Safari/535.1', '', '47806', '1', 'N'),
