('48061', '1979', 'Jason', 'enricopallazo@yahoo.com', 'http://www.jasonmjones.net', '65.242.114.226', '2011-11-03 08:43:07', '2011-11-03 12:43:07', 'I read BASS 2011 about a month ago, and honestly, I can\'t say that I really remember anything in it all that well, except maybe the Tin House stories, but that\'s because I subscribe to Tin House read those over the course of the previous year and the second reading reinforced my memory. My problem with the collection is how heavily New Yorker stories dominate every year. I\'m sorry, but with all the writing that\'s out there, do we really need 6 stories reprinted from the New Yorker (for as much as I love Tin House, I tend to feel they\'re a bit too Tin House heavy as well). I\'d like to see more diversity in terms of the magazines whose stories are selected. Hundreds of magazines send their work and we get 6 from the New Yorker and 3 from Tin House? (Okay, those numbers might be wrong, but I don\'t have a copy to references here with me). Also, a passing thought this year was that it bothered me that Granta gets considered (even though I\'ve really liked the issues of Granta). Since when does Granta meet the qualifications of set forth in the opening guidelines? I don\'t care if they\'ve opened an office in New York, they\'re a British mag, right? I feel like the BASS editors just made this exception for Granta based on reputation.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en-US; rv:1.9.2.3) Gecko/20100401 Firefox/3.6.3', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
