('48231', '2067', 'Dawn.', 'dawngrrrl@gmail.com', 'http://nouvelliste.tumblr.com', '75.180.24.47', '2011-12-04 12:25:42', '2011-12-04 16:25:42', '2. OMFG <i>Virgin Diaries</i>. I am both incredibly grossed out and can\'t stop giggling. On a side note: I don\'t even know OF any virgins anymore. Last time I knew a virgin I was 18. We both \"lost\" our virginity within like three months of one another. On a side-side note: I like how everyone makes such a BFD out of virginity because our culture is this creepy mix of perv, body shame, and violent sexual repression BUT, virginity isn\'t even real in the first place. Total cultural creation. Good job us.\r\n\r\n3. Ugh. Your experiences with the academics who are in denial about their racism and/or privilege are pretty much exactly like my experiences with white upper and middle class \"creative types,\" i.e. the vast majority of the people I\'m surrounded by thanks to my suburban childhood, being a little hipster in high school, and the tiny but \"prestigious\" liberal arts college I almost graduated from. So feeling you re: the total exhaustion.\r\n\r\nAlso: I hate the series, but your Twilight recap is fucking hilarious.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:8.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/8.0', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('48323', '2105', 'Tricia', 'triciaaho@lycos.com', '', '75.73.56.55', '2011-12-21 00:43:16', '2011-12-21 04:43:16', 'I loved this post.  I adore Love Actually so much. I think someone who doesn\'t would have to be mentally broken in one way or another. I know someone who knows someone who went to high school with Josh Duhamel. She let him copy her homework. He is very, very pretty. Thank you for the part about romantic movies being formulaic silliness, but still being enjoyable to watch. \r\n\r\nPlease forgive the random ramblings. This post has so many good things. Thanks for the entertaining read.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Linux; U; Android 2.1-update1; en-us; MB508 Build/Blur_Version.1.23.20.MB508.ATT.en.US Flex/P033) AppleWebKit/530.17 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Mobile Safari/530.17', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('48243', '2067', 'Teri C.', 'scouttlc@yahoo.com', 'http://tericarter.wordpress.com', '76.103.142.127', '2011-12-07 19:55:18', '2011-12-07 23:55:18', 'In my fantasy land I like to imagine it\'s not like this at colleges and universities, that the educated are better people.  Which is, of course, total bullshit.  A friend of mine works in Admissions at Southeast Missouri State, and it curdles all the hairs on my white girl arms when he tells me his \"stories.\"\r\n\r\nI live in northern California, but I\'m from southeast Missouri and it\'s still horrible there.  Since my mother died, I only go home about every 2 years so it\'s like a fresh dose of old language every time.  The stuff my family and their friends say in private is one thing, but the words out of their mouths in public -- and loudly and with laughter in public -- is still, always, a shock.  I went home last week for my grandfather\'s funeral.  All the old men were telling jokes in the back of the church with the little boys.  One joke was, \"Do you know what the little nigger boy said when he had diarrhea?  Mom, I\'m melting!\"  Their laughter brought the house down.  \r\n\r\nWhen I tell people in California that most everyone I know back home still uses the \"n\" word in regular conversation, they think I\'m exaggerating.  Who would exaggerate that?', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_7_2) AppleWebKit/534.51.22 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.1.1 Safari/534.51.22', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
('48244', '2067', 'Teri C.', 'scouttlc@yahoo.com', 'http://tericarter.wordpress.com', '76.103.142.127', '2011-12-07 19:59:50', '2011-12-07 23:59:50', 'I also meant to add that, all the time now, I hear this:  \"It\'s so much better since President Obama was elected.\"\r\n\r\nNo.  I\'m sorry.  It isn\'t.  It\'s worse.  My brother back home won\'t even tell me all the stuff he hears anymore, it\'s gotten so bad.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_7_2) AppleWebKit/534.51.22 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/5.1.1 Safari/534.51.22', '', '0', '0', 'N'),
