('48249', '2070', 'Jaimie', 'jlteekell@gmail.com', 'http://jaimieteekell.com', '76.202.11.37', '2011-12-08 10:54:32', '2011-12-08 14:54:32', 'Wait, you loved Twilight but you hated The Muppets? \r\n\r\n....\r\n\r\nWell, all right. I guess I can accept that. Muppets really don\'t make any sense and I would argue that they never really have. Maybe as an adult that bothers you more than when you were a kid? (Movie freak here.)\r\n\r\nYou know that horrible cartoon of Toy Story before The Muppets? Did that play in your theater? Because it sucked. And people were <i>laughing</i>. What is <i>wrong</i> with people. If you laugh at shit, the producers hear and they make more shit. <i>You don\'t laugh</i>. Just because it\'s all the old gang doing the voice-overs, and Jane Lynch too, doesn\'t make it creative. It was all the old themes of Toy Story we\'ve already seen, rehashed and unfunny. \"Not being played with sucks, I know, let\'s show a toy support group!\" No.\r\n\r\nMy mom used to make tons of wedding cakes growing up. Those holes in the cake don\'t mean you did anything wrong per se, but if you want them to not be there you do this: after you put the batter in the pan, shake the pan a bit and drop it a few inches onto the counter top. Repeat a few times. That gets the bubbles out, so voila. No holes.', '0', '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:8.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/8.0', '', '0', '0', 'Y'),
